var book = {
	"name": "1 Kings",
	"numChapters": 22,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>Now King David was old and advanced in years. And although they covered him with clothes, he could not get warm.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Therefore his servants said to him, “Let a young woman be sought for my lord the king, and let her wait on the king and be in his service. Let her lie in your arms, that my lord the king may be warm.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So they sought for a beautiful young woman throughout all the territory of Israel, and found Abishag the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8721A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8721A\"></sup>Shunammite, and brought her to the king.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The young woman was very beautiful, and she was of service to the king and attended to him, but the king knew her not.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8723B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8723B\"></sup>Adonijah the son of Haggith exalted himself, saying, “I will be king.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8723C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8723C\"></sup>And he prepared for himself chariots and horsemen, and fifty men to run before him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>His father had never at any time displeased him by asking, “Why have you done thus and so?” He was also a very handsome man, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8724D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8724D\"></sup>and he was born next after Absalom.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He conferred with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8725E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8725E\"></sup>Joab the son of Zeruiah and with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8725F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8725F\"></sup>Abiathar the priest. And they followed Adonijah and helped him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8726G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8726G\"></sup>Zadok the priest and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8726H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8726H\"></sup>Benaiah the son of Jehoiada and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8726I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8726I\"></sup>Nathan the prophet and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8726J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8726J\"></sup>Shimei and Rei and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8726K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8726K\"></sup>David's mighty men were not with Adonijah.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Adonijah sacrificed sheep, oxen, and fattened cattle by the Serpent's Stone, which is beside <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8727L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8727L\"></sup>En-rogel, and he invited all his brothers, the king's sons, and all the royal officials of Judah,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>but he did not invite Nathan the prophet or Benaiah or the mighty men or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8728M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8728M\"></sup>Solomon his brother.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Nathan said to Bathsheba the mother of Solomon, “Have you not heard that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8729N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8729N\"></sup>Adonijah the son of Haggith has become king and David our lord does not know it?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now therefore come, let me give you advice, that you may save your own life and the life of your son Solomon.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Go in at once to King David, and say to him, ‘Did you not, my lord the king, swear to your servant, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8731O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8731O\"></sup>“Solomon your son shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne”? Why then is Adonijah king?’",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then while you are still speaking with the king, I also will come in after you and confirm your words.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So Bathsheba went to the king in his chamber (now the king was very old, and Abishag the Shunammite was attending to the king).",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Bathsheba bowed and paid homage to the king, and the king said, “What do you desire?”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>She said to him, “My lord, you swore to your servant by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8735P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8735P\"></sup>‘Solomon your son shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne.’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And now, behold, Adonijah is king, although you, my lord the king, do not know it.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8737Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8737Q\"></sup>He has sacrificed oxen, fattened cattle, and sheep in abundance, and has invited all the sons of the king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8737R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8737R\"></sup>Abiathar the priest, and Joab the commander of the army, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8737S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8737S\"></sup>Solomon your servant he has not invited.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And now, my lord the king, the eyes of all Israel are on you, to tell them who shall sit on the throne of my lord the king after him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Otherwise it will come to pass, when my lord the king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8739T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8739T\"></sup>sleeps with his fathers, that I and my son Solomon will be counted offenders.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>While she was still speaking with the king, Nathan the prophet came in.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And they told the king, “Here is Nathan the prophet.” And when he came in before the king, he bowed before the king, with his face to the ground.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And Nathan said, “My lord the king, have you said, ‘Adonijah shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne’?",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For he has gone down this day and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8743U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8743U\"></sup>has sacrificed oxen, fattened cattle, and sheep in abundance, and has invited all the king's sons, the commanders of the army, and Abiathar the priest. And behold, they are eating and drinking before him, and saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8743V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8743V\"></sup>‘Long live King Adonijah!’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8744W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8744W\"></sup>But me, your servant, and Zadok the priest, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and your servant Solomon he has not invited.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Has this thing been brought about by my lord the king and you have not told your servants who should sit on the throne of my lord the king after him?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then King David answered, “Call Bathsheba to me.” So she came into the king's presence and stood before the king.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And the king swore, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8747X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8747X\"></sup>“As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, who has redeemed my soul out of every adversity,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8748Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8748Y\"></sup>as I swore to you by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, saying, ‘Solomon your son shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne in my place,’ even so will I do this day.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Bathsheba bowed with her face to the ground and paid homage to the king and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8749Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8749Z\"></sup>“May my lord King David live forever!”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>King David said, “Call to me Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada.” So they came before the king.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And the king said to them, “Take with you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8751AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8751AA\"></sup>the servants of your lord and have Solomon my son ride on my own mule, and bring him down to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8751AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8751AB\"></sup>Gihon.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And let Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8752AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8752AC\"></sup>anoint him king over Israel. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8752AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8752AD\"></sup>Then blow the trumpet and say, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8752AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8752AE\"></sup>‘Long live King Solomon!’",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>You shall then come up after him, and he shall come and sit on my throne, for he shall be king in my place. And I have appointed him to be ruler over Israel and over Judah.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And Benaiah the son of Jehoiada answered the king, “Amen! May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of my lord the king, say so.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8755AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8755AF\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has been with my lord the king, even so may he be with Solomon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8755AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8755AG\"></sup>and make his throne greater than the throne of my lord King David.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>So Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8756AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8756AH\"></sup>and the Cherethites and the Pelethites went down and had Solomon ride on King David's mule and brought him to Gihon.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>There Zadok the priest took the horn of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8757AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8757AI\"></sup>oil from the tent and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8757AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8757AJ\"></sup>anointed Solomon. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8757AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8757AK\"></sup>Then they blew the trumpet, and all the people said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8757AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8757AL\"></sup>“Long live King Solomon!”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And all the people went up after him, playing on pipes, and rejoicing with great joy, so that the earth was split by their noise.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Adonijah and all the guests who were with him heard it as they finished feasting. And when Joab heard the sound of the trumpet, he said, “What does this uproar in the city mean?”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>While he was still speaking, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8760AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8760AM\"></sup>Jonathan the son of Abiathar the priest came. And Adonijah said, “Come in, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8760AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8760AN\"></sup>for you are a worthy man and bring good news.”",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Jonathan answered Adonijah, “No, for our lord King David has made Solomon king,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>and the king has sent with him Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8762AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8762AO\"></sup>Cherethites and the Pelethites. And they had him ride on the king's mule.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>And Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet have anointed him king at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8763AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8763AP\"></sup>Gihon, and they have gone up from there rejoicing, so that the city is in an uproar. This is the noise that you have heard.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8764AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8764AQ\"></sup>Solomon sits on the royal throne.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Moreover, the king's servants came to congratulate our lord King David, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8765AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8765AR\"></sup>‘May your God make the name of Solomon more famous than yours, and make his throne greater than your throne.’ And the king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8765AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8765AS\"></sup>bowed himself on the bed.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>And the king also said, ‘Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8766AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8766AT\"></sup>who has granted someone to sit on my throne this day, my own eyes seeing it.’”",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Then all the guests of Adonijah trembled and rose, and each went his own way.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>And Adonijah feared Solomon. So he arose and went <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8768AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8768AU\"></sup>and took hold of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8768AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8768AV\"></sup>the horns of the altar.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Then it was told Solomon, “Behold, Adonijah fears King Solomon, for behold, he has laid hold of the horns of the altar, saying, ‘Let King Solomon swear to me first that he will not put his servant to death with the sword.’”",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>And Solomon said, “If he will show himself a worthy man, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8770AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8770AW\"></sup>not one of his hairs shall fall to the earth, but if wickedness is found in him, he shall die.”",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>So King Solomon sent, and they brought him down from the altar. And he came and paid homage to King Solomon, and Solomon said to him, “Go to your house.”"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8772A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8772A\"></sup>When David's time to die drew near, he commanded Solomon his son, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8773B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8773B\"></sup>“I am about to go the way of all the earth. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8773C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8773C\"></sup>Be strong, and show yourself a man,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and keep the charge of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, walking in his ways and keeping his statutes, his commandments, his rules, and his testimonies, as it is written in the Law of Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8774D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8774D\"></sup>that you may prosper in all that you do and wherever you turn,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8775E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8775E\"></sup>establish his word that he spoke concerning me, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8775F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8775F\"></sup>‘If your sons pay close attention to their way, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8775G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8775G\"></sup>to walk before me in faithfulness with all their heart and with all their soul, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8775H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8775H\"></sup>you shall not lack a man on the throne of Israel.’",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Moreover, you also know what Joab the son of Zeruiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8776I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8776I\"></sup>did to me, how he dealt with the two commanders of the armies of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8776J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8776J\"></sup>Abner the son of Ner, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8776K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8776K\"></sup>and Amasa the son of Jether, whom he killed, avenging in time of peace for blood that had been shed in war, and putting the blood of war on the belt around his waist and on the sandals on his feet.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Act therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8777L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8777L\"></sup>according to your wisdom, but do not let his gray head go down to Sheol in peace.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But deal loyally with the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8778M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8778M\"></sup>Barzillai the Gileadite, and let them be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8778N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8778N\"></sup>among those who eat at your table, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8778O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8778O\"></sup>for with such loyalty they met me when I fled from Absalom your brother.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And there is also with you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8779P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8779P\"></sup>Shimei the son of Gera, the Benjaminite from Bahurim, who cursed me with a grievous curse on the day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8779Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8779Q\"></sup>when I went to Mahanaim. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8779R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8779R\"></sup>But when he came down to meet me at the Jordan, I swore to him by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, ‘I will not put you to death with the sword.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now therefore do not hold him guiltless, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8780S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8780S\"></sup>for you are a wise man. You will know what you ought to do to him, and you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8780T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8780T\"></sup>bring his gray head down with blood to Sheol.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8781U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8781U\"></sup>Then David slept with his fathers and was buried in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8781V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8781V\"></sup>the city of David.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the time that David reigned over Israel was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8782W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8782W\"></sup>forty years. He reigned seven years in Hebron and thirty-three years in Jerusalem.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8783X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8783X\"></sup>So Solomon sat on the throne of David his father, and his kingdom was firmly established.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Adonijah the son of Haggith came to Bathsheba the mother of Solomon. And she said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8784Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8784Y\"></sup>“Do you come peacefully?” He said, “Peacefully.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then he said, “I have something to say to you.” She said, “Speak.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He said, “You know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8786Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8786Z\"></sup>the kingdom was mine, and that all Israel fully expected me to reign. However, the kingdom has turned about and become my brother's, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8786AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8786AA\"></sup>for it was his from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And now I have one request to make of you; do not refuse me.” She said to him, “Speak.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he said, “Please ask King Solomon—he will not refuse you—to give me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8788AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8788AB\"></sup>Abishag the Shunammite as my wife.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Bathsheba said, “Very well; I will speak for you to the king.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So Bathsheba went to King Solomon to speak to him on behalf of Adonijah. And the king rose to meet her and bowed down to her. Then he sat on his throne and had a seat brought for the king's mother, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8790AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8790AC\"></sup>and she sat on his right.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then she said, “I have one small request to make of you; do not refuse me.” And the king said to her, “Make your request, my mother, for I will not refuse you.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>She said, “Let <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8792AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8792AD\"></sup>Abishag the Shunammite be given to Adonijah your brother as his wife.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>King Solomon answered his mother, “And why do you ask <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8793AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8793AE\"></sup>Abishag the Shunammite for Adonijah? Ask for him the kingdom also, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8793AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8793AF\"></sup>for he is my older brother, and on his side <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8793AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8793AG\"></sup>are Abiathar the priest and Joab the son of Zeruiah.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then King Solomon swore by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8794AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8794AH\"></sup>“God do so to me and more also if this word does not cost Adonijah his life!",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Now therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8795AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8795AI\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, who has established me and placed me on the throne of David my father, and who has made me a house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8795AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8795AJ\"></sup>as he promised, Adonijah shall be put to death today.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So King Solomon sent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8796AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8796AK\"></sup>Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and he struck him down, and he died.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And to Abiathar the priest the king said, “Go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8797AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8797AL\"></sup>Anathoth, to your estate, for you deserve death. But I will not at this time put you to death, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8797AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8797AM\"></sup>because you carried the ark of the Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span> before David my father, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8797AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8797AN\"></sup>and because you shared in all my father's affliction.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8798AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8798AO\"></sup>So Solomon expelled Abiathar from being priest to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, thus fulfilling <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8798AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8798AP\"></sup>the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he had spoken concerning the house of Eli in Shiloh.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When the news came to Joab—for Joab <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8799AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8799AQ\"></sup>had supported Adonijah although <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8799AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8799AR\"></sup>he had not supported Absalom—Joab fled to the tent of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and caught hold of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8799AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8799AS\"></sup>horns of the altar.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And when it was told King Solomon, “Joab has fled to the tent of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and behold, he is beside the altar,” Solomon sent Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, saying, “Go, strike him down.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So Benaiah came to the tent of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said to him, “The king commands, ‘Come out.’” But he said, “No, I will die here.” Then Benaiah brought the king word again, saying, “Thus said Joab, and thus he answered me.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The king replied to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8802AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8802AT\"></sup>“Do as he has said, strike him down and bury him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8802AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8802AU\"></sup>and thus take away from me and from my father's house the guilt for the blood that Joab shed without cause.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8803AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8803AV\"></sup>bring back his bloody deeds on his own head, because, without the knowledge of my father David, he attacked and killed with the sword two men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8803AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8803AW\"></sup>more righteous and better than himself, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8803AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8803AX\"></sup>Abner the son of Ner, commander of the army of Israel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8803AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8803AY\"></sup>Amasa the son of Jether, commander of the army of Judah.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8804AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8804AZ\"></sup>So shall their blood come back on the head of Joab and on the head of his descendants forever. But for David and for his descendants and for his house and for his throne there shall be peace from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forevermore.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then Benaiah the son of Jehoiada went up and struck him down and put him to death. And he was buried in his own house in the wilderness.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8806BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8806BA\"></sup>The king put Benaiah the son of Jehoiada over the army in place of Joab, and the king put <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8806BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8806BB\"></sup>Zadok the priest <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8806BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8806BC\"></sup>in the place of Abiathar.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then the king sent and summoned <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8807BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8807BD\"></sup>Shimei and said to him, “Build yourself a house in Jerusalem and dwell there, and do not go out from there to any place whatever.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>For on the day you go out and cross <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8808BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8808BE\"></sup>the brook Kidron, know for certain that you shall die. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8808BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8808BF\"></sup>Your blood shall be on your own head.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And Shimei said to the king, “What you say is good; as my lord the king has said, so will your servant do.” So Shimei lived in Jerusalem many days.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>But it happened at the end of three years that two of Shimei's servants ran away to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8810BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8810BG\"></sup>Achish, son of Maacah, king of Gath. And when it was told Shimei, “Behold, your servants are in Gath,”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Shimei arose and saddled a donkey and went to Gath to Achish to seek his servants. Shimei went and brought his servants from Gath.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And when Solomon was told that Shimei had gone from Jerusalem to Gath and returned,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>the king sent and summoned Shimei and said to him, “Did I not make you swear by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and solemnly warn you, saying, ‘Know for certain that on the day you go out and go to any place whatever, you shall die’? And you said to me, ‘What you say is good; I will obey.’",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Why then have you not kept your oath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the commandment with which I commanded you?”",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>The king also said to Shimei, “You know in your own heart <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8815BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8815BH\"></sup>all the harm that you did to David my father. So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8815BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8815BI\"></sup>bring back your harm on your own head.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>But King Solomon shall be blessed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8816BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8816BJ\"></sup>and the throne of David shall be established before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forever.”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Then the king commanded Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and he went out and struck him down, and he died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8817BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8817BK\"></sup>So the kingdom was established in the hand of Solomon."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8818A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8818A\"></sup>Solomon made a marriage alliance with Pharaoh king of Egypt. He took Pharaoh's daughter and brought her into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8818B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8818B\"></sup>the city of David until he had finished <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8818C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8818C\"></sup>building his own house <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8818D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8818D\"></sup>and the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8818E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8818E\"></sup>and the wall around Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8819F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8819F\"></sup>The people were sacrificing at the high places, however, because no house had yet been built for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Solomon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8820G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8820G\"></sup>loved the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8820H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8820H\"></sup>walking in the statutes of David his father, only he sacrificed and made offerings at the high places.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And the king went to Gibeon to sacrifice there, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8821I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8821I\"></sup>for that was the great high place. Solomon used to offer a thousand burnt offerings on that altar.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8822J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8822J\"></sup>At Gibeon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8822K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8822K\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to Solomon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8822L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8822L\"></sup>in a dream by night, and God said, “Ask what I shall give you.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Solomon said, “You have shown great and steadfast love to your servant David my father, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8823M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8823M\"></sup>he walked before you in faithfulness, in righteousness, and in uprightness of heart toward you. And you have kept for him this great and steadfast love and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8823N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8823N\"></sup>have given him a son to sit on his throne this day.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And now, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8824O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8824O\"></sup>you have made your servant king in place of David my father, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8824P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8824P\"></sup>although I am but a little child. I do not know <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8824Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8824Q\"></sup>how to go out or come in.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8825R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8825R\"></sup>And your servant is in the midst of your people whom you have chosen, a great people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8825S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8825S\"></sup>too many to be numbered or counted for multitude.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8826T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8826T\"></sup>Give your servant therefore an understanding mind <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8826U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8826U\"></sup>to govern your people, that I may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8826V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8826V\"></sup>discern between good and evil, for who is able to govern this your great people?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>It pleased the Lord that Solomon had asked this.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And God said to him, “Because you have asked this, and have not asked for yourself long life or riches or the life of your enemies, but have asked for yourself understanding to discern what is right,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8829W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8829W\"></sup>I now do according to your word. Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8829X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8829X\"></sup>I give you a wise and discerning mind, so that none like you has been before you and none like you shall arise after you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8830Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8830Y\"></sup>I give you also what you have not asked, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8830Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8830Z\"></sup>both riches and honor, so that no other king shall compare with you, all your days.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And if you will walk in my ways, keeping my statutes and my commandments, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8831AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8831AA\"></sup>as your father David walked, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8831AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8831AB\"></sup>I will lengthen your days.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Solomon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8832AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8832AC\"></sup>awoke, and behold, it was a dream. Then he came to Jerusalem and stood before the ark of the covenant of the Lord, and offered up burnt offerings and peace offerings, and made a feast for all his servants.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then two prostitutes came to the king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8833AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8833AD\"></sup>and stood before him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The one woman said, “Oh, my lord, this woman and I live in the same house, and I gave birth to a child while she was in the house.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then on the third day after I gave birth, this woman also gave birth. And we were alone. There was no one else with us in the house; only we two were in the house.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And this woman's son died in the night, because she lay on him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And she arose at midnight and took my son from beside me, while your servant slept, and laid him at her breast, and laid her dead son at my breast.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When I rose in the morning to nurse my child, behold, he was dead. But when I looked at him closely in the morning, behold, he was not the child that I had borne.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But the other woman said, “No, the living child is mine, and the dead child is yours.” The first said, “No, the dead child is yours, and the living child is mine.” Thus they spoke before the king.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then the king said, “The one says, ‘This is my son that is alive, and your son is dead’; and the other says, ‘No; but your son is dead, and my son is the living one.’”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the king said, “Bring me a sword.” So a sword was brought before the king.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And the king said, “Divide the living child in two, and give half to the one and half to the other.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then the woman whose son was alive said to the king, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8843AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8843AE\"></sup>her heart yearned for her son, “Oh, my lord, give her the living child, and by no means put him to death.” But the other said, “He shall be neither mine nor yours; divide him.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then the king answered and said, “Give the living child to the first woman, and by no means put him to death; she is his mother.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And all Israel heard of the judgment that the king had rendered, and they stood in awe of the king, because they perceived that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8845AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8845AF\"></sup>the wisdom of God was in him to do justice."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>King Solomon was king over all Israel,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and these were his high officials: Azariah the son of Zadok was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8847A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8847A\"></sup>the priest;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Elihoreph and Ahijah the sons of Shisha were secretaries; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8848B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8848B\"></sup>Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud was recorder;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8849C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8849C\"></sup>Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was in command of the army; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8849D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8849D\"></sup>Zadok and Abiathar were priests;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Azariah the son of Nathan was over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8850E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8850E\"></sup>the officers; Zabud the son of Nathan was priest and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8850F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8850F\"></sup>king's friend;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Ahishar was in charge of the palace; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8851G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8851G\"></sup>Adoniram the son of Abda was in charge of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8851H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8851H\"></sup>the forced labor.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Solomon had twelve officers over all Israel, who provided food for the king and his household. Each man had to make provision for one month in the year.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>These were their names: Ben-hur, in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8853I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8853I\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Ben-deker, in Makaz, Shaalbim, Beth-shemesh, and Elonbeth-hanan;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Ben-hesed, in Arubboth (to him belonged Socoh and all the land of Hepher);",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Ben-abinadab, in all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8856J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8856J\"></sup>Naphath-dor (he had Taphath the daughter of Solomon as his wife);",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Baana the son of Ahilud, in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8857K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8857K\"></sup>Taanach, Megiddo, and all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8857L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8857L\"></sup>Beth-shean that is beside Zarethan below Jezreel, and from Beth-shean to Abel-meholah, as far as the other side of Jokmeam;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Ben-geber, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8858M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8858M\"></sup>in Ramoth-gilead (he had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8858N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8858N\"></sup>the villages of Jair the son of Manasseh, which are in Gilead, and he had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8858O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8858O\"></sup>the region of Argob, which is in Bashan, sixty great cities with walls and bronze bars);",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Ahinadab the son of Iddo, in Mahanaim;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Ahimaaz, in Naphtali (he had taken Basemath the daughter of Solomon as his wife);",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Baana the son of Hushai, in Asher and Bealoth;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Jehoshaphat the son of Paruah, in Issachar;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8863P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8863P\"></sup>Shimei the son of Ela, in Benjamin;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Geber the son of Uri, in the land of Gilead, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8864Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8864Q\"></sup>the country of Sihon king of the Amorites and of Og king of Bashan. And there was one governor who was over the land.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Judah and Israel were as many <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8865R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8865R\"></sup>as the sand by the sea. They ate and drank and were happy.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8866S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8866S\"></sup>Solomon ruled over all the kingdoms from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8866T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8866T\"></sup>Euphrates to the land of the Philistines and to the border of Egypt. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8866U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8866U\"></sup>They brought tribute and served Solomon all the days of his life.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Solomon's provision for one day was thirty cors of fine flour and sixty cors of meal,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>ten fat oxen, and twenty pasture-fed cattle, a hundred sheep, besides deer, gazelles, roebucks, and fattened fowl.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For he had dominion over all the region west of the Euphrates from Tiphsah to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8869V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8869V\"></sup>Gaza, over all the kings west of the Euphrates. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8869W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8869W\"></sup>And he had peace on all sides around him.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And Judah and Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8870X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8870X\"></sup>lived in safety, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8870Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8870Y\"></sup>from Dan even to Beersheba, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8870Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8870Z\"></sup>every man under his vine and under his fig tree, all the days of Solomon.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8871AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8871AA\"></sup>Solomon also had 40,000 stalls of horses for his chariots, and 12,000 horsemen.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And those officers supplied provisions for King Solomon, and for all who came to King Solomon's table, each one in his month. They let nothing be lacking.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Barley also and straw for the horses and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8873AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8873AB\"></sup>swift steeds they brought to the place where it was required, each according to his duty.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8874AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8874AC\"></sup>And God gave Solomon wisdom and understanding beyond measure, and breadth of mind <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8874AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8874AD\"></sup>like the sand on the seashore,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>so that Solomon's wisdom surpassed the wisdom of all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8875AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8875AE\"></sup>the people of the east <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8875AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8875AF\"></sup>and all the wisdom of Egypt.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For he was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8876AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8876AG\"></sup>wiser than all other men, wiser than Ethan the Ezrahite, and Heman, Calcol, and Darda, the sons of Mahol, and his fame was in all the surrounding nations.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8877AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8877AH\"></sup>He also spoke 3,000 proverbs, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8877AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8877AI\"></sup>and his songs were 1,005.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He spoke of trees, from the cedar that is in Lebanon to the hyssop that grows out of the wall. He spoke also of beasts, and of birds, and of reptiles, and of fish.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And people of all nations came to hear the wisdom of Solomon, and from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8879AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8879AJ\"></sup>all the kings of the earth, who had heard of his wisdom."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span> Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8880A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8880A\"></sup>Hiram king of Tyre sent his servants to Solomon when he heard that they had anointed him king in place of his father, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8880B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8880B\"></sup>for Hiram always loved David.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Solomon sent word to Hiram,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8882C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8882C\"></sup>“You know that David my father could not build a house for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8882D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8882D\"></sup>because of the warfare with which his enemies surrounded him, until the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> put them under the soles of his feet.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8883E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8883E\"></sup>But now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God has given me rest on every side. There is neither adversary nor misfortune.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And so I intend to build a house for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8884F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8884F\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to David my father, ‘Your son, whom I will set on your throne in your place, shall build the house for my name.’",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now therefore command that cedars of Lebanon be cut for me. And my servants will join your servants, and I will pay you for your servants such wages as you set, for you know that there is no one among us who knows how to cut timber like the Sidonians.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>As soon as Hiram heard the words of Solomon, he rejoiced greatly and said, “Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> this day, who has given to David a wise son to be over this great people.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Hiram sent to Solomon, saying, “I have heard the message that you have sent to me. I am ready to do all you desire in the matter of cedar and cypress timber.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>My servants shall bring it down to the sea from Lebanon, and I will make it into rafts to go by sea to the place you direct. And I will have them broken up there, and you shall receive it. And you shall meet my wishes <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8888G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8888G\"></sup>by providing food for my household.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So Hiram supplied Solomon with all the timber of cedar and cypress that he desired,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>while Solomon gave Hiram 20,000 cors of wheat as food for his household, and 20,000 cors of beaten oil. Solomon gave this to Hiram year by year.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave Solomon wisdom, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8891H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8891H\"></sup>as he promised him. And there was peace between Hiram and Solomon, and the two of them made a treaty.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>King Solomon drafted <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8892I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8892I\"></sup>forced labor out of all Israel, and the draft numbered 30,000 men.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And he sent them to Lebanon, 10,000 a month in shifts. They would be a month in Lebanon and two months at home. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8893J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8893J\"></sup>Adoniram was in charge of the draft.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Solomon also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8894K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8894K\"></sup>had 70,000 burden-bearers and 80,000 stonecutters in the hill country,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>besides Solomon's 3,300 <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8895L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8895L\"></sup>chief officers who were over the work, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8895M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8895M\"></sup>who had charge of the people who carried on the work.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>At the king's command <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8896N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8896N\"></sup>they quarried out great, costly stones in order to lay the foundation of the house with dressed stones.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So Solomon's builders and Hiram's builders and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8897O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8897O\"></sup>the men of Gebal did the cutting and prepared the timber and the stone to build the house."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8898A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8898A\"></sup>In the four hundred and eightieth year after the people of Israel came out of the land of Egypt, in the fourth year of Solomon's reign over Israel, in the month of Ziv, which is the second month, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8898B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8898B\"></sup>he began to build the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8899C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8899C\"></sup>The house that King Solomon built for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was sixty cubits long, twenty cubits wide, and thirty cubits high.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The vestibule in front of the nave of the house was twenty cubits long, equal to the width of the house, and ten cubits deep in front of the house.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8901D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8901D\"></sup>he made for the house windows with recessed frames.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8902E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8902E\"></sup>He also built a structure against the wall of the house, running around the walls of the house, both the nave and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8902F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8902F\"></sup>the inner sanctuary. And he made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8902G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8902G\"></sup>side chambers all around.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The lowest story was five cubits broad, the middle one was six cubits broad, and the third was seven cubits broad. For around the outside of the house he made offsets on the wall in order that the supporting beams should not be inserted into the walls of the house.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the house was built, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8904H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8904H\"></sup>it was with stone prepared at the quarry, so that neither hammer nor axe nor any tool of iron was heard in the house while it was being built.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The entrance for the lowest story was on the south side of the house, and one went up by stairs to the middle story, and from the middle story to the third.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8906I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8906I\"></sup>So he built the house and finished it, and he made the ceiling of the house of beams and planks of cedar.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He built the structure against the whole house, five cubits high, and it was joined to the house with timbers of cedar.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Solomon,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“Concerning this house that you are building, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8909J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8909J\"></sup>if you will walk in my statutes and obey my rules and keep all my commandments and walk in them, then I will establish my word with you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8909K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8909K\"></sup>which I spoke to David your father.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8910L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8910L\"></sup>I will dwell among the children of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8910M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8910M\"></sup>and will not forsake my people Israel.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8911N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8911N\"></sup>So Solomon built the house and finished it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He lined the walls of the house on the inside with boards of cedar. From the floor of the house to the walls of the ceiling, he covered them on the inside with wood, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8912O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8912O\"></sup>and he covered the floor of the house with boards of cypress.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8913P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8913P\"></sup>He built twenty cubits of the rear of the house with boards of cedar from the floor to the walls, and he built this within as an inner sanctuary, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8913Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8913Q\"></sup>the Most Holy Place.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The house, that is, the nave in front of the inner sanctuary, was forty cubits long.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The cedar within the house was carved in the form of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8915R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8915R\"></sup>gourds and open flowers. All was cedar; no stone was seen.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The inner sanctuary he prepared in the innermost part of the house, to set there the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The inner sanctuary was twenty cubits long, twenty cubits wide, and twenty cubits high, and he overlaid it with pure gold. He also overlaid an altar of cedar.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And Solomon overlaid the inside of the house with pure gold, and he drew chains of gold across, in front of the inner sanctuary, and overlaid it with gold.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And he overlaid the whole house with gold, until all the house was finished. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8919S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8919S\"></sup>Also the whole altar that belonged to the inner sanctuary he overlaid with gold.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8920T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8920T\"></sup>In the inner sanctuary <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8920U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8920U\"></sup>he made two cherubim of olivewood, each ten cubits high.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Five cubits was the length of one wing of the cherub, and five cubits the length of the other wing of the cherub; it was ten cubits from the tip of one wing to the tip of the other.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The other cherub also measured ten cubits; both cherubim had the same measure and the same form.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The height of one cherub was ten cubits, and so was that of the other cherub.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He put the cherubim in the innermost part of the house. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8924V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8924V\"></sup>And the wings of the cherubim were spread out so that a wing of one touched the one wall, and a wing of the other cherub touched the other wall; their other wings touched each other in the middle of the house.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And he overlaid the cherubim with gold.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Around all the walls of the house he carved engraved figures of cherubim and palm trees and open flowers, in the inner and outer rooms.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The floor of the house he overlaid with gold in the inner and outer rooms.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For the entrance to the inner sanctuary he made doors of olivewood; the lintel and the doorposts were five-sided.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He covered the two doors of olivewood with carvings of cherubim, palm trees, and open flowers. He overlaid them with gold and spread gold on the cherubim and on the palm trees.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So also he made for the entrance to the nave doorposts of olivewood, in the form of a square,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>and two doors of cypress wood. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8931W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8931W\"></sup>The two leaves of the one door were folding, and the two leaves of the other door were folding.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>On them he carved cherubim and palm trees and open flowers, and he overlaid them with gold evenly applied on the carved work.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8933X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8933X\"></sup>He built the inner court with three courses of cut stone and one course of cedar beams.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8934Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8934Y\"></sup>In the fourth year the foundation of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was laid, in the month of Ziv.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And in the eleventh year, in the month of Bul, which is the eighth month, the house was finished in all its parts, and according to all its specifications. He was seven years in building it."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>Solomon was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8936A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8936A\"></sup>building his own house thirteen years, and he finished his entire house.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8937B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8937B\"></sup>the House of the Forest of Lebanon. Its length was a hundred cubits and its breadth fifty cubits and its height thirty cubits, and it was built on four rows of cedar pillars, with cedar beams on the pillars.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And it was covered with cedar above the chambers that were on the forty-five pillars, fifteen in each row.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>There were window frames in three rows, and window opposite window in three tiers.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>All the doorways and windows had square frames, and window was opposite window in three tiers.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8941C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8941C\"></sup>the Hall of Pillars; its length was fifty cubits, and its breadth thirty cubits. There was a porch in front with pillars, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8941D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8941D\"></sup>a canopy in front of them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And he made the Hall of the Throne where he was to pronounce judgment, even the Hall of Judgment. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8942E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8942E\"></sup>It was finished with cedar from floor to rafters.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>His own house where he was to dwell, in the other court back of the hall, was of like workmanship. Solomon also made a house like this hall for Pharaoh's daughter <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8943F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8943F\"></sup>whom he had taken in marriage.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>All these were made of costly stones, cut according to measure, sawed with saws, back and front, even from the foundation to the coping, and from the outside to the great court.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The foundation was of costly stones, huge stones, stones of eight and ten cubits.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And above were costly stones, cut according to measurement, and cedar.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8947G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8947G\"></sup>The great court had three courses of cut stone all around, and a course of cedar beams; so had the inner court of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8947H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8947H\"></sup>the vestibule of the house.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And King Solomon sent and brought <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8948I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8948I\"></sup>Hiram from Tyre.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He was the son of a widow of the tribe of Naphtali, and his father was a man of Tyre, a worker in bronze. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8949J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8949J\"></sup>he was full of wisdom, understanding, and skill for making any work in bronze. He came to King Solomon and did all his work.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8950K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8950K\"></sup>He cast <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8950L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8950L\"></sup>two pillars of bronze. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8950M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8950M\"></sup>Eighteen cubits was the height of one pillar, and a line of twelve cubits measured its circumference. It was hollow, and its thickness was four fingers. The second pillar was the same.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He also made two capitals of cast bronze to set on the tops of the pillars. The height of the one capital was five cubits, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8951N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8951N\"></sup>the height of the other capital was five cubits.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>There were lattices of checker work with wreaths of chain work for the capitals on the tops of the pillars, a lattice for the one capital and a lattice for the other capital.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Likewise he made pomegranates in two rows around the one latticework to cover the capital that was on the top of the pillar, and he did the same with the other capital.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now the capitals that were on the tops of the pillars in the vestibule were of lily-work, four cubits.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The capitals were on the two pillars and also above the rounded projection which was beside the latticework. There were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8955O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8955O\"></sup>two hundred pomegranates in two rows all around, and so with the other capital.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8956P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8956P\"></sup>He set up the pillars at the vestibule of the temple. He set up the pillar on the south and called its name Jachin, and he set up the pillar on the north and called its name Boaz.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And on the tops of the pillars was lily-work. Thus the work of the pillars was finished.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8958Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8958Q\"></sup>Then he made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8958R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8958R\"></sup>the sea of cast metal. It was round, ten cubits from brim to brim, and five cubits high, and a line of thirty cubits measured its circumference.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Under its brim were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8959S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8959S\"></sup>gourds, for ten cubits, compassing the sea all around. The gourds were in two rows, cast with it when it was cast.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>It stood on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8960T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8960T\"></sup>twelve oxen, three facing north, three facing west, three facing south, and three facing east. The sea was set on them, and all their rear parts were inward.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Its thickness was a handbreadth, and its brim was made like the brim of a cup, like the flower of a lily. It held two thousand baths.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He also made the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8962U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8962U\"></sup>ten stands of bronze. Each stand was four cubits long, four cubits wide, and three cubits high.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>This was the construction of the stands: they had panels, and the panels were set in the frames,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and on the panels that were set in the frames were lions, oxen, and cherubim. On the frames, both above and below the lions and oxen, there were wreaths of beveled work.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Moreover, each stand had four bronze wheels and axles of bronze, and at the four corners were supports for a basin. The supports were cast with wreaths at the side of each.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Its opening was within a crown that projected upward one cubit. Its opening was round, as a pedestal is made, a cubit and a half deep. At its opening there were carvings, and its panels were square, not round.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And the four wheels were underneath the panels. The axles of the wheels were of one piece with the stands, and the height of a wheel was a cubit and a half.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The wheels were made like a chariot wheel; their axles, their rims, their spokes, and their hubs were all cast.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>There were four supports at the four corners of each stand. The supports were of one piece with the stands.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And on the top of the stand there was a round band half a cubit high; and on the top of the stand its stays and its panels were of one piece with it.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And on the surfaces of its stays and on its panels, he carved cherubim, lions, and palm trees, according to the space of each, with wreaths all around.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>After this manner he made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8972V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8972V\"></sup>the ten stands. All of them were cast alike, of the same measure and the same form.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And he made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8973W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8973W\"></sup>ten basins of bronze. Each basin held forty baths, each basin measured four cubits, and there was a basin for each of the ten stands.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And he set the stands, five on the south side of the house, and five on the north side of the house. And he set the sea at the southeast corner of the house.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8975X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8975X\"></sup>Hiram also made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8975Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8975Y\"></sup>the pots, the shovels, and the basins. So Hiram finished all the work that he did for King Solomon on the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>:",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>the two pillars, the two bowls of the capitals that were on the tops of the pillars, and the two <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8976Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8976Z\"></sup>latticeworks to cover the two bowls of the capitals that were on the tops of the pillars;",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8977AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8977AA\"></sup>four hundred pomegranates for the two latticeworks, two rows of pomegranates for each latticework, to cover the two bowls of the capitals that were on the pillars;",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>the ten stands, and the ten basins on the stands;",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8979AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8979AB\"></sup>the one sea, and the twelve oxen underneath the sea.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8980AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8980AC\"></sup>the pots, the shovels, and the basins, all these vessels in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which Hiram made for King Solomon, were of burnished bronze.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>In the plain of the Jordan the king cast them, in the clay ground between <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8981AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8981AD\"></sup>Succoth and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8981AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8981AE\"></sup>Zarethan.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>And Solomon left all the vessels unweighed, because there were so many of them; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8982AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8982AF\"></sup>the weight of the bronze was not ascertained.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>So Solomon made all the vessels that were in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8983AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8983AG\"></sup>the golden altar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8983AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8983AH\"></sup>the golden table for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8983AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8983AI\"></sup>the bread of the Presence,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8984AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8984AJ\"></sup>the lampstands of pure gold, five on the south side and five on the north, before the inner sanctuary; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8984AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8984AK\"></sup>the flowers, the lamps, and the tongs, of gold;",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>the cups, snuffers, basins, dishes for incense, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8985AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8985AL\"></sup>fire pans, of pure gold; and the sockets of gold, for the doors of the innermost part of the house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8985AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8985AM\"></sup>the Most Holy Place, and for the doors of the nave of the temple.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Thus all the work that King Solomon did on the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was finished. And Solomon brought in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8986AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8986AN\"></sup>the things that David his father had dedicated, the silver, the gold, and the vessels, and stored them in the treasuries of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8987A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8987A\"></sup>Then Solomon assembled the elders of Israel and all the heads of the tribes, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8987B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8987B\"></sup>the leaders of the fathers' houses of the people of Israel, before King Solomon in Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8987C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8987C\"></sup>to bring up the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> out of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8987D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8987D\"></sup>the city of David, which is Zion.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And all the men of Israel assembled to King Solomon at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8988E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8988E\"></sup>the feast in the month Ethanim, which is the seventh month.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And all the elders of Israel came, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8989F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8989F\"></sup>the priests took up the ark.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And they brought up the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8990G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8990G\"></sup>the tent of meeting, and all the holy vessels that were in the tent; the priests and the Levites brought them up.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And King Solomon and all the congregation of Israel, who had assembled before him, were with him before the ark, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8991H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8991H\"></sup>sacrificing so many sheep and oxen that they could not be counted or numbered.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8992I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8992I\"></sup>Then the priests brought the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8992J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8992J\"></sup>to its place in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8992K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8992K\"></sup>the inner sanctuary of the house, in the Most Holy Place, underneath the wings of the cherubim.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For the cherubim spread out their wings over the place of the ark, so that the cherubim overshadowed the ark and its poles.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8994L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8994L\"></sup>And the poles were so long that the ends of the poles were seen from the Holy Place before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8994M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8994M\"></sup>the inner sanctuary; but they could not be seen from outside. And they are there to this day.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>There was nothing in the ark except <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8995N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8995N\"></sup>the two tablets of stone that Moses put there at Horeb, where <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8995O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8995O\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made a covenant with the people of Israel, when they came out of the land of Egypt.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And when the priests came out of the Holy Place, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8996P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8996P\"></sup>a cloud filled the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>so that the priests could not stand to minister because of the cloud, for the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> filled the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8998Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8998Q\"></sup>Then Solomon said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has said that he would dwell <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8998R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8998R\"></sup>in thick darkness.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8999S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8999S\"></sup>I have indeed built you an exalted house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8999T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8999T\"></sup>a place for you to dwell in forever.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the king turned around and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9000U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9000U\"></sup>blessed all the assembly of Israel, while all the assembly of Israel stood.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9001V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9001V\"></sup>“Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, who with his hand has fulfilled <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9001W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9001W\"></sup>what he promised with his mouth to David my father, saying,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9002X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9002X\"></sup>‘Since the day that I brought my people Israel out of Egypt, I chose no city out of all the tribes of Israel in which to build a house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9002Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9002Y\"></sup>that my name might be there. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9002Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9002Z\"></sup>But I chose David to be over my people Israel.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9003AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9003AA\"></sup>Now it was in the heart of David my father to build a house for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to David my father, ‘Whereas it was in your heart to build a house for my name, you did well that it was in your heart.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9005AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9005AB\"></sup>Nevertheless, you shall not build the house, but your son who shall be born to you shall build the house for my name.’",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has fulfilled his promise that he made. For I have risen in the place of David my father, and sit on the throne of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9006AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9006AC\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> promised, and I have built the house for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And there I have provided a place for the ark, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9007AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9007AD\"></sup>in which is the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he made with our fathers, when he brought them out of the land of Egypt.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Solomon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9008AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9008AE\"></sup>stood before the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the presence of all the assembly of Israel and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9008AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9008AF\"></sup>spread out his hands toward heaven,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9009AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9009AG\"></sup>there is no God like you, in heaven above or on earth beneath, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9009AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9009AH\"></sup>keeping covenant and showing steadfast love to your servants who walk before you with all their heart;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>you have kept with your servant David my father what you declared to him. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9010AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9010AI\"></sup>You spoke with your mouth, and with your hand have fulfilled it this day.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now therefore, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God of Israel, keep for your servant David my father what you have promised him, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9011AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9011AJ\"></sup>‘You shall not lack a man to sit before me on the throne of Israel, if only your sons pay close attention to their way, to walk before me as you have walked before me.’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9012AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9012AK\"></sup>Now therefore, O God of Israel, let your word be confirmed, which you have spoken to your servant David my father.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“But will God indeed dwell on the earth? Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9013AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9013AL\"></sup>heaven and the highest heaven cannot contain you; how much less this house that I have built!",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Yet have regard to the prayer of your servant and to his plea, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, listening to the cry and to the prayer that your servant prays before you this day,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9015AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9015AM\"></sup>that your eyes may be open night and day toward this house, the place of which you have said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9015AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9015AN\"></sup>‘My name shall be there,’ that you may listen to the prayer that your servant offers toward this place.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And listen to the plea of your servant and of your people Israel, when they pray toward this place. And listen in heaven your dwelling place, and when you hear, forgive.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“If a man sins against his neighbor and is made to take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9017AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9017AO\"></sup>an oath and comes and swears his oath before your altar in this house,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>then hear in heaven and act and judge your servants, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9018AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9018AP\"></sup>condemning the guilty by bringing his conduct on his own head, and vindicating the righteous by rewarding him according to his righteousness.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9019AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9019AQ\"></sup>“When your people Israel are defeated before the enemy because they have sinned against you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9019AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9019AR\"></sup>if they turn again to you and acknowledge your name and pray and plead with you in this house,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>then hear in heaven and forgive the sin of your people Israel and bring them again to the land that you gave to their fathers.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9021AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9021AS\"></sup>“When heaven is shut up and there is no rain because they have sinned against you, if they pray toward this place and acknowledge your name and turn from their sin, when you afflict them,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>then hear in heaven and forgive the sin of your servants, your people Israel, when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9022AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9022AT\"></sup>you teach them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9022AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9022AU\"></sup>the good way in which they should walk, and grant rain upon your land, which you have given to your people as an inheritance.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9023AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9023AV\"></sup>“If there is famine in the land, if there is pestilence or blight or mildew or locust or caterpillar, if their enemy besieges them in the land at their gates, whatever plague, whatever sickness there is,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>whatever prayer, whatever plea is made by any man or by all your people Israel, each knowing the affliction of his own heart and stretching out his hands toward this house,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>then hear in heaven your dwelling place and forgive and act and render to each whose heart you know, according to all his ways (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9025AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9025AW\"></sup>for you, you only, know the hearts of all the children of mankind),",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>that they may fear you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9026AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9026AX\"></sup>all the days that they live in the land that you gave to our fathers.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“Likewise, when a foreigner, who is not of your people Israel, comes from a far country for your name's sake",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>(for they shall hear of your great name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9028AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9028AY\"></sup>and your mighty hand, and of your outstretched arm), when he comes and prays toward this house,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>hear in heaven your dwelling place and do according to all for which the foreigner calls to you, in order <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9029AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9029AZ\"></sup>that all the peoples of the earth may know your name and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9029BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9029BA\"></sup>fear you, as do your people Israel, and that they may know that this house that I have built is called by your name.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>“If your people go out to battle against their enemy, by whatever way you shall send them, and they pray to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9030BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9030BB\"></sup>toward the city that you have chosen and the house that I have built for your name,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>then hear in heaven their prayer and their plea, and maintain their cause.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>“If they sin against you—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9032BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9032BC\"></sup>for there is no one who does not sin—and you are angry with them and give them to an enemy, so that they are carried away captive <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9032BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9032BD\"></sup>to the land of the enemy, far off or near,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9033BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9033BE\"></sup>if they turn their heart in the land to which they have been carried captive, and repent and plead with you in the land of their captors, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9033BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9033BF\"></sup>‘We have sinned and have acted perversely and wickedly,’",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9034BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9034BG\"></sup>if they repent with all their heart and with all their soul in the land of their enemies, who carried them captive, and pray to you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9034BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9034BH\"></sup>toward their land, which you gave to their fathers, the city that you have chosen, and the house that I have built for your name,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>then hear in heaven your dwelling place their prayer and their plea, and maintain their cause",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>and forgive your people who have sinned against you, and all their transgressions that they have committed against you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9036BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9036BI\"></sup>grant them compassion in the sight of those who carried them captive, that they may have compassion on them",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>(<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9037BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9037BJ\"></sup>for they are your people, and your heritage, which you brought out of Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9037BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9037BK\"></sup>from the midst of the iron furnace).",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9038BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9038BL\"></sup>Let your eyes be open to the plea of your servant and to the plea of your people Israel, giving ear to them whenever they call to you.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>For you separated them from among all the peoples of the earth to be your heritage, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9039BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9039BM\"></sup>as you declared through Moses your servant, when you brought our fathers out of Egypt, O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>.”",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9040BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9040BN\"></sup>Now as Solomon finished offering all this prayer and plea to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he arose from before the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, where he had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9040BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9040BO\"></sup>knelt with hands outstretched toward heaven.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>And he stood and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9041BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9041BP\"></sup>blessed all the assembly of Israel with a loud voice, saying,",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>“Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who has given rest to his people Israel, according to all that he promised. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9042BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9042BQ\"></sup>Not one word has failed of all his good promise, which he spoke by Moses his servant.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God be with us, as he was with our fathers. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9043BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9043BR\"></sup>May he not leave us or forsake us,",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>that he may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9044BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9044BS\"></sup>incline our hearts to him, to walk in all his ways and to keep his commandments, his statutes, and his rules, which he commanded our fathers.",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>Let these words of mine, with which I have pleaded before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, be near to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God day and night, and may he maintain the cause of his servant and the cause of his people Israel, as each day requires,",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9046BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9046BT\"></sup>all the peoples of the earth may know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9046BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9046BU\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is God; there is no other.",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9047BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9047BV\"></sup>Let your heart therefore be wholly true to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, walking in his statutes and keeping his commandments, as at this day.”",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9048BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9048BW\"></sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9048BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9048BX\"></sup>the king, and all Israel with him, offered sacrifice before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>Solomon offered as peace offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> 22,000 oxen and 120,000 sheep. So the king and all the people of Israel dedicated the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>The same day the king consecrated the middle of the court that was before the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for there he offered the burnt offering and the grain offering and the fat pieces of the peace offerings, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9050BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9050BY\"></sup>the bronze altar that was before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was too small to receive the burnt offering and the grain offering and the fat pieces of the peace offerings.",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>So Solomon held <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9051BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9051BZ\"></sup>the feast at that time, and all Israel with him, a great assembly, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9051CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9051CA\"></sup>Lebo-hamath to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9051CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9051CB\"></sup>the Brook of Egypt, before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, seven days.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>On the eighth day he sent the people away, and they blessed the king and went to their homes joyful and glad of heart for all the goodness that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had shown to David his servant and to Israel his people."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9053A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9053A\"></sup>As soon as Solomon had finished building the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9053B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9053B\"></sup>and the king's house and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9053C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9053C\"></sup>all that Solomon desired to build,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9054D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9054D\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to Solomon a second time, as he had appeared to him at Gibeon.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “I have heard your prayer and your plea, which you have made before me. I have consecrated this house that you have built, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9055E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9055E\"></sup>by putting my name there forever. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9055F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9055F\"></sup>My eyes and my heart will be there for all time.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And as for you, if you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9056G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9056G\"></sup>walk before me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9056H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9056H\"></sup>as David your father walked, with integrity of heart and uprightness, doing according to all that I have commanded you, and keeping my statutes and my rules,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9057I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9057I\"></sup>then I will establish your royal throne over Israel forever, as I promised David your father, saying, ‘You shall not lack a man on the throne of Israel.’",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9058J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9058J\"></sup>But if you turn aside from following me, you or your children, and do not keep my commandments and my statutes that I have set before you, but go and serve other gods and worship them,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9059K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9059K\"></sup>then I will cut off Israel from the land that I have given them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9059L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9059L\"></sup>and the house that I have consecrated for my name I will cast out of my sight, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9059M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9059M\"></sup>and Israel will become a proverb and a byword among all peoples.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And this house will become a heap of ruins. Everyone passing by it will be astonished and will hiss, and they will say, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9060N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9060N\"></sup>‘Why has the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> done thus to this land and to this house?’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then they will say, ‘Because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9061O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9061O\"></sup>they abandoned the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God who brought their fathers out of the land of Egypt and laid hold on other gods and worshiped them and served them. Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has brought all this disaster on them.’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9062P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9062P\"></sup>At the end of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9062Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9062Q\"></sup>twenty years, in which Solomon had built the two houses, the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the king's house,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and Hiram king of Tyre had supplied Solomon with cedar and cypress timber and gold, as much as he desired, King Solomon gave to Hiram twenty cities in the land of Galilee.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But when Hiram came from Tyre to see the cities that Solomon had given him, they did not please him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Therefore he said, “What kind of cities are these that you have given me, my brother?” So they are called the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9065R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9065R\"></sup>Cabul to this day.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Hiram had sent to the king 120 talents of gold.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And this is the account of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9067S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9067S\"></sup>the forced labor that King Solomon drafted to build the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and his own house and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9067T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9067T\"></sup>the Millo and the wall of Jerusalem and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9067U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9067U\"></sup>Hazor and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9067V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9067V\"></sup>Megiddo and Gezer",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>(Pharaoh king of Egypt had gone up and captured Gezer and burned it with fire, and had killed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9068W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9068W\"></sup>the Canaanites who lived in the city, and had given it as dowry to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9068X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9068X\"></sup>his daughter, Solomon's wife;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>so Solomon rebuilt Gezer) and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9069Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9069Y\"></sup>Lower Beth-horon",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and Baalath and Tamar in the wilderness, in the land of Judah,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and all the store cities that Solomon had, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9071Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9071Z\"></sup>the cities for his chariots, and the cities for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9071AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9071AA\"></sup>his horsemen, and whatever Solomon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9071AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9071AB\"></sup>desired to build in Jerusalem, in Lebanon, and in all the land of his dominion.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>All the people who were left of the Amorites, the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites, who were not of the people of Israel—",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9073AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9073AC\"></sup>their descendants who were left after them in the land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9073AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9073AD\"></sup>whom the people of Israel were unable to devote to destruction—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9073AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9073AE\"></sup>these Solomon drafted to be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9073AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9073AF\"></sup>slaves, and so they are to this day.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9074AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9074AG\"></sup>of the people of Israel Solomon made no slaves. They were the soldiers, they were his officials, his commanders, his captains, his chariot commanders and his horsemen.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>These were the chief officers who were over Solomon's work: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9075AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9075AH\"></sup>550 <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9075AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9075AI\"></sup>who had charge of the people who carried on the work.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9076AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9076AJ\"></sup>Pharaoh's daughter went up from the city of David to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9076AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9076AK\"></sup>her own house that Solomon had built for her. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9076AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9076AL\"></sup>Then he built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9076AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9076AM\"></sup>the Millo.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Three times a year Solomon used to offer up burnt offerings and peace offerings on the altar that he built to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, making offerings with it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. So he finished the house.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>King Solomon built a fleet of ships at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9078AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9078AN\"></sup>Ezion-geber, which is near Eloth on the shore of the Red Sea, in the land of Edom.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And Hiram sent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9079AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9079AO\"></sup>with the fleet his servants, seamen who were familiar with the sea, together with the servants of Solomon.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And they went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9080AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9080AP\"></sup>Ophir and brought from there gold, 420 talents, and they brought it to King Solomon."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9081A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9081A\"></sup>Now when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9081B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9081B\"></sup>the queen of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9081C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9081C\"></sup>Sheba heard of the fame of Solomon concerning the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, she came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9081D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9081D\"></sup>to test him with hard questions.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>She came to Jerusalem with a very great retinue, with camels <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9082E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9082E\"></sup>bearing spices and very much gold and precious stones. And when she came to Solomon, she told him all that was on her mind.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Solomon answered all her questions; there was nothing hidden from the king that he could not explain to her.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And when the queen of Sheba had seen all the wisdom of Solomon, the house that he had built,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>the food of his table, the seating of his officials, and the attendance of his servants, their clothing, his cupbearers, and his burnt offerings that he offered at the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, there was no more breath in her.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And she said to the king, “The report was true that I heard in my own land of your words and of your wisdom,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>but I did not believe the reports until I came and my own eyes had seen it. And behold, the half was not told me. Your wisdom and prosperity surpass the report that I heard.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9088F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9088F\"></sup>Happy are your men! Happy are your servants, who continually stand before you and hear your wisdom!",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9089G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9089G\"></sup>Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who has delighted in you and set you on the throne of Israel! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9089H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9089H\"></sup>Because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> loved Israel forever, he has made you king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9089I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9089I\"></sup>that you may execute justice and righteousness.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9090J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9090J\"></sup>Then she gave the king 120 talents of gold, and a very great quantity of spices and precious stones. Never again came such an abundance of spices as these that the queen of Sheba gave to King Solomon.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9091K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9091K\"></sup>the fleet of Hiram, which brought <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9091L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9091L\"></sup>gold from Ophir, brought from Ophir a very great amount of almug wood and precious stones.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the king made of the almug wood supports for the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for the king's house, also lyres and harps for the singers. No such almug wood has come or been seen to this day.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And King Solomon gave to the queen of Sheba all that she desired, whatever she asked besides what was given her by the bounty of King Solomon. So she turned and went back to her own land with her servants.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9094M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9094M\"></sup>Now the weight of gold that came to Solomon in one year was 666 talents of gold,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>besides that which came from the explorers and from the business of the merchants, and from all the kings of the west and from the governors of the land.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>King Solomon made 200 large shields of beaten gold; 600 shekels of gold went into each shield.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he made 300 <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9097N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9097N\"></sup>shields of beaten gold; three minas of gold went into each shield. And the king put them in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9097O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9097O\"></sup>the House of the Forest of Lebanon.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The king also made a great ivory throne and overlaid it with the finest gold.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The throne had six steps, and the throne had a round top, and on each side of the seat were armrests and two lions standing beside the armrests,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>while twelve lions stood there, one on each end of a step on the six steps. The like of it was never made in any kingdom.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>All King Solomon's drinking vessels were of gold, and all the vessels of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9101P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9101P\"></sup>the House of the Forest of Lebanon were of pure gold. None were of silver; silver was not considered as anything in the days of Solomon.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For the king had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9102Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9102Q\"></sup>a fleet of ships of Tarshish at sea with the fleet of Hiram. Once every three years the fleet of ships of Tarshish used to come bringing gold, silver, ivory, apes, and peacocks.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9103R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9103R\"></sup>Thus King Solomon excelled all the kings of the earth in riches and in wisdom.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the whole earth sought the presence of Solomon to hear his wisdom, which God had put into his mind.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Every one of them brought his present, articles of silver and gold, garments, myrrh, spices, horses, and mules, so much year by year.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9106S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9106S\"></sup>And Solomon gathered together <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9106T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9106T\"></sup>chariots and horsemen. He had 1,400 chariots and 12,000 horsemen, whom he stationed in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9106U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9106U\"></sup>chariot cities and with the king in Jerusalem.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And the king made silver as common in Jerusalem as stone, and he made cedar as plentiful as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9107V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9107V\"></sup>the sycamore of the Shephelah.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And Solomon's <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9108W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9108W\"></sup>import of horses was from Egypt and Kue, and the king's traders received them from Kue at a price.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>A chariot could be imported from Egypt for 600 shekels of silver and a horse for 150, and so through the king's traders they were exported to all the kings of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9109X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9109X\"></sup>the Hittites and the kings of Syria."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9110A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9110A\"></sup>King Solomon loved many foreign women, along with the daughter of Pharaoh: Moabite, Ammonite, Edomite, Sidonian, and Hittite women,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>from the nations concerning which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said to the people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9111B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9111B\"></sup>“You shall not enter into marriage with them, neither shall they with you, for surely they will turn away your heart after their gods.” Solomon clung to these in love.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He had 700 wives, who were princesses, and 300 concubines. And his wives turned away his heart.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For when Solomon was old his wives turned away his heart after other gods, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9113C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9113C\"></sup>his heart was not wholly true to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9113D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9113D\"></sup>as was the heart of David his father.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For Solomon went after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9114E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9114E\"></sup>Ashtoreth the goddess of the Sidonians, and after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9114F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9114F\"></sup>Milcom the abomination of the Ammonites.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Solomon did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and did not wholly follow the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as David his father had done.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Solomon built a high place for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9116G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9116G\"></sup>Chemosh the abomination of Moab, and for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9116H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9116H\"></sup>Molech the abomination of the Ammonites, on the mountain east of Jerusalem.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And so he did for all his foreign wives, who made offerings and sacrificed to their gods.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was angry with Solomon, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9118I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9118I\"></sup>his heart had turned away from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9118J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9118J\"></sup>who had appeared to him twice",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9119K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9119K\"></sup>had commanded him concerning this thing, that he should not go after other gods. But he did not keep what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Solomon, “Since this has been your practice and you have not kept my covenant and my statutes that I have commanded you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9120L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9120L\"></sup>I will surely tear the kingdom from you and will give it to your servant.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Yet for the sake of David your father I will not do it in your days, but I will tear it out of the hand of your son.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>However, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9122M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9122M\"></sup>I will not tear away all the kingdom, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9122N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9122N\"></sup>I will give one tribe to your son, for the sake of David my servant and for the sake of Jerusalem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9122O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9122O\"></sup>that I have chosen.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> raised up an adversary against Solomon, Hadad the Edomite. He was of the royal house in Edom.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9124P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9124P\"></sup>when David was in Edom, and Joab the commander of the army went up to bury the slain, he struck down every male in Edom",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>(for Joab and all Israel remained there six months, until he had cut off every male in Edom).",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But Hadad fled to Egypt, together with certain Edomites of his father's servants, Hadad still being a little child.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They set out from Midian and came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9127Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9127Q\"></sup>Paran and took men with them from Paran and came to Egypt, to Pharaoh king of Egypt, who gave him a house and assigned him an allowance of food and gave him land.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And Hadad found great favor in the sight of Pharaoh, so that he gave him in marriage the sister of his own wife, the sister of Tahpenes the queen.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the sister of Tahpenes bore him Genubath his son, whom Tahpenes weaned in Pharaoh's house. And Genubath was in Pharaoh's house among the sons of Pharaoh.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But when Hadad heard in Egypt <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9130R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9130R\"></sup>that David slept with his fathers and that Joab the commander of the army was dead, Hadad said to Pharaoh, “Let me depart, that I may go to my own country.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But Pharaoh said to him, “What have you lacked with me that you are now seeking to go to your own country?” And he said to him, “Only let me depart.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>God also raised up as an adversary to him, Rezon the son of Eliada, who had fled from his master <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9132S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9132S\"></sup>Hadadezer king of Zobah.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And he gathered men about him and became leader of a marauding band, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9133T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9133T\"></sup>after the killing by David. And they went to Damascus and lived there and made him king in Damascus.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He was an adversary of Israel all the days of Solomon, doing harm as Hadad did. And he loathed Israel and reigned over Syria.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9135U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9135U\"></sup>Jeroboam the son of Nebat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9135V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9135V\"></sup>an Ephraimite of Zeredah, a servant of Solomon, whose mother's name was Zeruah, a widow, also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9135W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9135W\"></sup>lifted up his hand against the king.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And this was the reason why he lifted up his hand against the king. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9136X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9136X\"></sup>Solomon built the Millo, and closed up the breach of the city of David his father.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The man Jeroboam was very able, and when Solomon saw that the young man was industrious he gave him charge over all the forced labor of the house of Joseph.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And at that time, when Jeroboam went out of Jerusalem, the prophet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9138Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9138Y\"></sup>Ahijah the Shilonite found him on the road. Now Ahijah had dressed himself in a new garment, and the two of them were alone in the open country.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Ahijah laid hold of the new garment that was on him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9139Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9139Z\"></sup>and tore it into twelve pieces.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And he said to Jeroboam, “Take for yourself ten pieces, for thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, ‘Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9140AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9140AA\"></sup>I am about to tear the kingdom from the hand of Solomon and will give you ten tribes",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>(but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9141AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9141AB\"></sup>he shall have one tribe, for the sake of my servant David and for the sake of Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9141AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9141AC\"></sup>the city that I have chosen out of all the tribes of Israel),",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>because they have forsaken me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9142AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9142AD\"></sup>and worshiped Ashtoreth the goddess of the Sidonians, Chemosh the god of Moab, and Milcom the god of the Ammonites, and they have not walked in my ways, doing what is right in my sight and keeping my statutes and my rules, as David his father did.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Nevertheless, I will not take the whole kingdom out of his hand, but I will make him ruler all the days of his life, for the sake of David my servant whom I chose, who kept my commandments and my statutes.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9144AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9144AE\"></sup>But I will take the kingdom out of his son's hand and will give it to you, ten tribes.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Yet to his son <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9145AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9145AF\"></sup>I will give one tribe, that David my servant may always have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9145AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9145AG\"></sup>a lamp before me in Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9145AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9145AH\"></sup>the city where I have chosen to put my name.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And I will take you, and you shall reign over all that your soul desires, and you shall be king over Israel.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And if you will listen to all that I command you, and will walk in my ways, and do what is right in my eyes by keeping my statutes and my commandments, as David my servant did, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9147AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9147AI\"></sup>I will be with you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9147AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9147AJ\"></sup>will build you a sure house, as I built for David, and I will give Israel to you.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And I will afflict the offspring of David because of this, but not forever.’”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Solomon sought therefore to kill Jeroboam. But Jeroboam arose and fled into Egypt, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9149AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9149AK\"></sup>Shishak king of Egypt, and was in Egypt until the death of Solomon.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9150AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9150AL\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Solomon, and all that he did, and his wisdom, are they not written in the Book of the Acts of Solomon?",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And the time that Solomon reigned in Jerusalem over all Israel was forty years.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And Solomon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9152AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9152AM\"></sup>slept with his fathers and was buried in the city of David his father. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9152AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9152AN\"></sup>Rehoboam his son reigned in his place."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9153A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9153A\"></sup>Rehoboam went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9153B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9153B\"></sup>Shechem, for all Israel had come to Shechem to make him king.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And as soon as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9154C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9154C\"></sup>Jeroboam the son of Nebat heard of it (for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9154D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9154D\"></sup>he was still in Egypt, where he had fled from King Solomon), then Jeroboam returned from Egypt.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And they sent and called him, and Jeroboam and all the assembly of Israel came and said to Rehoboam,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9156E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9156E\"></sup>“Your father made our yoke heavy. Now therefore lighten the hard service of your father and his heavy yoke on us, and we will serve you.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9157F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9157F\"></sup>“Go away for three days, then come again to me.” So the people went away.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then King Rehoboam took counsel with the old men, who had stood before Solomon his father while he was yet alive, saying, “How do you advise me to answer this people?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And they said to him, “If you will be a servant to this people today and serve them, and speak good words to them when you answer them, then they will be your servants forever.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But he abandoned the counsel that the old men gave him and took counsel with the young men who had grown up with him and stood before him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And he said to them, “What do you advise that we answer this people who have said to me, ‘Lighten the yoke that your father put on us’?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the young men who had grown up with him said to him, “Thus shall you speak to this people who said to you, ‘Your father made our yoke heavy, but you lighten it for us,’ thus shall you say to them, ‘My little finger is thicker than my father's thighs.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And now, whereas <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9163G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9163G\"></sup>my father laid on you a heavy yoke, I will add to your yoke. My father disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline you with scorpions.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So Jeroboam and all the people came to Rehoboam the third day, as the king said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9164H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9164H\"></sup>“Come to me again the third day.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the king answered the people harshly, and forsaking the counsel that the old men had given him,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>he spoke to them according to the counsel of the young men, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9166I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9166I\"></sup>“My father made your yoke heavy, but I will add to your yoke. My father disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline you with scorpions.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So the king did not listen to the people, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9167J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9167J\"></sup>it was a turn of affairs brought about by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he might fulfill his word, which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9167K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9167K\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke by Ahijah the Shilonite to Jeroboam the son of Nebat.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And when all Israel saw that the king did not listen to them, the people answered the king, “What portion do we have in David? We have no inheritance in the son of Jesse. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9168L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9168L\"></sup>To your tents, O Israel! Look now to your own house, David.” So Israel went to their tents.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But Rehoboam reigned over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9169M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9169M\"></sup>the people of Israel who lived in the cities of Judah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then King Rehoboam sent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9170N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9170N\"></sup>Adoram, who was taskmaster over the forced labor, and all Israel stoned him to death with stones. And King Rehoboam hurried to mount his chariot to flee to Jerusalem.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9171O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9171O\"></sup>So Israel has been in rebellion against the house of David to this day.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And when all Israel heard that Jeroboam had returned, they sent and called him to the assembly and made him king over all Israel. There was none that followed the house of David but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9172P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9172P\"></sup>the tribe of Judah only.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9173Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9173Q\"></sup>When Rehoboam came to Jerusalem, he assembled all the house of Judah and the tribe of Benjamin, 180,000 chosen warriors, to fight against the house of Israel, to restore the kingdom to Rehoboam the son of Solomon.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But the word of God came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9174R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9174R\"></sup>Shemaiah the man of God:",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Say to Rehoboam the son of Solomon, king of Judah, and to all the house of Judah and Benjamin, and to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9175S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9175S\"></sup>rest of the people,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, You shall not go up or fight against your relatives the people of Israel. Every man return to his home, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9176T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9176T\"></sup>for this thing is from me.’” So they listened to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and went home again, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Jeroboam <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9177U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9177U\"></sup>built Shechem in the hill country of Ephraim and lived there. And he went out from there and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9177V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9177V\"></sup>built Penuel.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And Jeroboam said in his heart, “Now the kingdom will turn back to the house of David.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>If this people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9179W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9179W\"></sup>go up to offer sacrifices in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at Jerusalem, then the heart of this people will turn again to their lord, to Rehoboam king of Judah, and they will kill me and return to Rehoboam king of Judah.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So the king took counsel and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9180X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9180X\"></sup>made two calves of gold. And he said to the people, “You have gone up to Jerusalem long enough. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9180Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9180Y\"></sup>Behold your gods, O Israel, who brought you up out of the land of Egypt.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And he set one in Bethel, and the other he put in Dan.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9182Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9182Z\"></sup>this thing became a sin, for the people went as far as Dan to be before one.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>He also made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9183AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9183AA\"></sup>temples on high places and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9183AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9183AB\"></sup>appointed priests from among all the people, who were not of the Levites.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And Jeroboam appointed a feast on the fifteenth day of the eighth month like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9184AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9184AC\"></sup>the feast that was in Judah, and he offered sacrifices on the altar. So he did in Bethel, sacrificing to the calves that he made. And he placed in Bethel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9184AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9184AD\"></sup>the priests of the high places that he had made.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He went up to the altar that he had made in Bethel on the fifteenth day in the eighth month, in the month that he had devised from his own heart. And he instituted a feast for the people of Israel and went up to the altar <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9185AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9185AE\"></sup>to make offerings."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>And behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9186A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9186A\"></sup>a man of God came out of Judah by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to Bethel. Jeroboam was standing by the altar <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9186B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9186B\"></sup>to make offerings.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9187C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9187C\"></sup>And the man cried against the altar by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, “O altar, altar, thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: ‘Behold, a son shall be born to the house of David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9187D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9187D\"></sup>Josiah by name, and he shall sacrifice on you the priests of the high places who make offerings on you, and human bones shall be burned on you.’”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And he gave <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9188E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9188E\"></sup>a sign the same day, saying, “This is the sign that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken: ‘Behold, the altar shall be torn down, and the ashes that are on it shall be poured out.’”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And when the king heard the saying of the man of God, which he cried against the altar at Bethel, Jeroboam stretched out his hand from the altar, saying, “Seize him.” And his hand, which he stretched out against him, dried up, so that he could not draw it back to himself.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The altar also was torn down, and the ashes poured out from the altar, according to the sign that the man of God had given by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the king said to the man of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9191F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9191F\"></sup>“Entreat now the favor of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and pray for me, that my hand may be restored to me.” And the man of God entreated the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the king's hand was restored to him and became as it was before.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the king said to the man of God, “Come home with me, and refresh yourself, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9192G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9192G\"></sup>I will give you a reward.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the man of God said to the king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9193H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9193H\"></sup>“If you give me half your house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9193I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9193I\"></sup>I will not go in with you. And I will not eat bread or drink water in this place,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>for so was it commanded me by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, ‘You shall neither eat bread nor drink water nor return by the way that you came.’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So he went another way and did not return by the way that he came to Bethel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9196J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9196J\"></sup>an old prophet lived in Bethel. And his sons came and told him all that the man of God had done that day in Bethel. They also told to their father the words that he had spoken to the king.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And their father said to them, “Which way did he go?” And his sons showed him the way that the man of God who came from Judah had gone.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And he said to his sons, “Saddle the donkey for me.” So they saddled the donkey for him and he mounted it.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And he went after the man of God and found him sitting under an oak. And he said to him, “Are you the man of God who came from Judah?” And he said, “I am.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then he said to him, “Come home with me and eat bread.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9201K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9201K\"></sup>“I may not return with you, or go in with you, neither will I eat bread nor drink water with you in this place,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>for it was said to me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9202L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9202L\"></sup>by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘You shall neither eat bread nor drink water there, nor return by the way that you came.’”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And he said to him, “I also am a prophet as you are, and an angel spoke to me by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, ‘Bring him back with you into your house that he may eat bread and drink water.’” But he lied to him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So he went back with him and ate bread in his house and drank water.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And as they sat at the table, the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to the prophet who had brought him back.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And he cried to the man of God who came from Judah, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘Because you have disobeyed the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and have not kept the command that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God commanded you,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>but have come back and have eaten bread and drunk water in the place of which he said to you, “Eat no bread and drink no water,” your body shall not come to the tomb of your fathers.’”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And after he had eaten bread and drunk, he saddled the donkey for the prophet whom he had brought back.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And as he went away <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9209M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9209M\"></sup>a lion met him on the road and killed him. And his body was thrown in the road, and the donkey stood beside it; the lion also stood beside the body.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And behold, men passed by and saw the body thrown in the road and the lion standing by the body. And they came and told it in the city where <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9210N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9210N\"></sup>the old prophet lived.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And when the prophet who had brought him back from the way heard of it, he said, “It is the man of God who disobeyed the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given him to the lion, which has torn him and killed him, according to the word that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to him.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And he said to his sons, “Saddle the donkey for me.” And they saddled it.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And he went and found his body thrown in the road, and the donkey and the lion standing beside the body. The lion had not eaten the body or torn the donkey.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And the prophet took up the body of the man of God and laid it on the donkey and brought it back to the city to mourn and to bury him.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And he laid the body in his own grave. And they mourned over him, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9215O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9215O\"></sup>“Alas, my brother!”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And after he had buried him, he said to his sons, “When I die, bury me in the grave in which the man of God is buried; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9216P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9216P\"></sup>lay my bones beside his bones.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9217Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9217Q\"></sup>For the saying that he called out by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> against the altar in Bethel and against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9217R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9217R\"></sup>all the houses of the high places that are in the cities of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9217S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9217S\"></sup>Samaria shall surely come to pass.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>After this thing Jeroboam did not turn from his evil way, but made priests for the high places again from among all the people. Any who would, he ordained to be priests of the high places.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9219T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9219T\"></sup>And this thing became sin to the house of Jeroboam, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9219U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9219U\"></sup>so as to cut it off and to destroy it from the face of the earth."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>At that time Abijah the son of Jeroboam fell sick.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Jeroboam said to his wife, “Arise, and disguise yourself, that it not be known that you are the wife of Jeroboam, and go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9221A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9221A\"></sup>Shiloh. Behold, Ahijah the prophet is there, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9221B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9221B\"></sup>who said of me that I should be king over this people.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9222C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9222C\"></sup>Take with you ten loaves, some cakes, and a jar of honey, and go to him. He will tell you what shall happen to the child.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Jeroboam's wife did so. She arose and went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9223D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9223D\"></sup>Shiloh and came to the house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9223E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9223E\"></sup>Ahijah. Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9223F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9223F\"></sup>Ahijah could not see, for his eyes were dim because of his age.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9224G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9224G\"></sup>Ahijah, “Behold, the wife of Jeroboam is coming to inquire of you concerning her son, for he is sick. Thus and thus shall you say to her.”When she came, she pretended to be another woman.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9225H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9225H\"></sup>Ahijah heard the sound of her feet, as she came in at the door, he said, “Come in, wife of Jeroboam. Why do you pretend to be another? For I am charged with unbearable news for you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Go, tell Jeroboam, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9226I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9226I\"></sup>“Because I exalted you from among the people and made you leader over my people Israel",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9227J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9227J\"></sup>tore the kingdom away from the house of David and gave it to you, and yet you have not been <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9227K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9227K\"></sup>like my servant David, who kept my commandments and followed me with all his heart, doing only that which was right in my eyes,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>but you have done evil above all who were before you and have gone and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9228L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9228L\"></sup>made for yourself other gods and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9228M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9228M\"></sup>metal images, provoking me to anger, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9228N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9228N\"></sup>have cast me behind your back,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>therefore behold, I will bring harm upon the house of Jeroboam and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9229O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9229O\"></sup>will cut off from Jeroboam every male, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9229P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9229P\"></sup>both bond and free in Israel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9229Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9229Q\"></sup>will burn up the house of Jeroboam, as a man burns up dung until it is all gone.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9230R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9230R\"></sup>Anyone belonging to Jeroboam who dies in the city the dogs shall eat, and anyone who dies in the open country the birds of the heavens shall eat, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken it.”’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Arise therefore, go to your house. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9231S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9231S\"></sup>When your feet enter the city, the child shall die.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And all Israel shall mourn for him and bury him, for he only of Jeroboam shall come to the grave, because in him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9232T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9232T\"></sup>there is found something pleasing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, in the house of Jeroboam.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9233U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9233U\"></sup>Moreover, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will raise up for himself a king over Israel who shall cut off the house of Jeroboam today. And henceforth,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will strike Israel as a reed is shaken in the water, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9234V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9234V\"></sup>root up Israel out of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9234W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9234W\"></sup>this good land that he gave to their fathers and scatter them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9234X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9234X\"></sup>beyond the Euphrates, because they have made their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9234Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9234Y\"></sup>Asherim, provoking the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to anger.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And he will give Israel up because of the sins of Jeroboam, which he sinned and made Israel to sin.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Jeroboam's wife arose and departed and came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9236Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9236Z\"></sup>Tirzah. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9236AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9236AA\"></sup>as she came to the threshold of the house, the child died.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And all Israel buried him and mourned for him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9237AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9237AB\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which he spoke by his servant Ahijah the prophet.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jeroboam, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9238AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9238AC\"></sup>how he warred and how he reigned, behold, they are written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the time that Jeroboam reigned was twenty-two years. And he slept with his fathers, and Nadab his son reigned in his place.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9240AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9240AD\"></sup>Now Rehoboam the son of Solomon reigned in Judah. Rehoboam was forty-one years old when he began to reign, and he reigned seventeen years in Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9240AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9240AE\"></sup>the city that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had chosen out of all the tribes of Israel, to put his name there. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9240AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9240AF\"></sup>His mother's name was Naamah the Ammonite.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9241AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9241AG\"></sup>And Judah did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9241AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9241AH\"></sup>provoked him to jealousy with their sins that they committed, more than all that their fathers had done.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For they also built for themselves <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9242AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9242AI\"></sup>high places <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9242AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9242AJ\"></sup>and pillars and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9242AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9242AK\"></sup>Asherim on every high hill and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9242AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9242AL\"></sup>under every green tree,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and there were also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9243AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9243AM\"></sup>male cult prostitutes in the land. They did according to all the abominations of the nations that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> drove out before the people of Israel.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9244AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9244AN\"></sup>In the fifth year of King Rehoboam, Shishak king of Egypt came up against Jerusalem.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He took away the treasures of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the treasures of the king's house. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9245AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9245AO\"></sup>He took away everything. He also took away all the shields of gold <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9245AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9245AP\"></sup>that Solomon had made,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and King Rehoboam made in their place shields of bronze, and committed them to the hands of the officers of the guard, who kept the door of the king's house.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And as often as the king went into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the guard carried them and brought them back to the guardroom.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9248AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9248AQ\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Rehoboam and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9249AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9249AR\"></sup>And there was war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam continually.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And Rehoboam slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers in the city of David. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9250AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9250AS\"></sup>His mother's name was Naamah the Ammonite. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9250AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9250AT\"></sup>Abijam his son reigned in his place."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9251A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9251A\"></sup>Now in the eighteenth year of King Jeroboam the son of Nebat, Abijam began to reign over Judah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He reigned for three years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Maacah the daughter of Abishalom.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And he walked in all the sins that his father did before him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9253B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9253B\"></sup>his heart was not wholly true to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, as the heart of David his father.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Nevertheless, for David's sake the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God gave him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9254C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9254C\"></sup>a lamp in Jerusalem, setting up his son after him, and establishing Jerusalem,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9255D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9255D\"></sup>David did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and did not turn aside from anything that he commanded him all the days of his life, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9255E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9255E\"></sup>except in the matter of Uriah the Hittite.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9256F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9256F\"></sup>Now there was war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam all the days of his life.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9257G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9257G\"></sup>The rest of the acts of Abijam and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9257H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9257H\"></sup>And there was war between Abijam and Jeroboam.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9258I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9258I\"></sup>And Abijam slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the city of David. And Asa his son reigned in his place.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>In the twentieth year of Jeroboam king of Israel, Asa began to reign over Judah,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and he reigned forty-one years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Maacah the daughter of Abishalom.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9261J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9261J\"></sup>And Asa did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as David his father had done.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He put away the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9262K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9262K\"></sup>male cult prostitutes out of the land and removed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9262L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9262L\"></sup>all the idols that his fathers had made.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9263M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9263M\"></sup>He also removed Maacah his mother from being queen mother because she had made an abominable image for Asherah. And Asa cut down her image and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9263N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9263N\"></sup>burned it at the brook Kidron.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9264O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9264O\"></sup>But the high places were not taken away. Nevertheless, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9264P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9264P\"></sup>the heart of Asa was wholly true to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all his days.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9265Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9265Q\"></sup>he brought into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the sacred gifts of his father and his own sacred gifts, silver, and gold, and vessels.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9266R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9266R\"></sup>And there was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their days.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9267S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9267S\"></sup>Baasha king of Israel went up against Judah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9267T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9267T\"></sup>built Ramah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9267U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9267U\"></sup>that he might permit no one to go out or come in to Asa king of Judah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Asa took all the silver and the gold <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9268V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9268V\"></sup>that were left in the treasures of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the treasures of the king's house and gave them into the hands of his servants. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9268W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9268W\"></sup>And King Asa sent them to Ben-hadad the son of Tabrimmon, the son of Hezion, king of Syria, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9268X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9268X\"></sup>who lived in Damascus, saying,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Let there be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9269Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9269Y\"></sup>a covenant between me and you, as there was between my father and your father. Behold, I am sending to you a present of silver and gold. Go, break your covenant with Baasha king of Israel, that he may withdraw from me.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And Ben-hadad listened to King Asa and sent the commanders of his armies against the cities of Israel and conquered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9270Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9270Z\"></sup>Ijon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9270AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9270AA\"></sup>Dan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9270AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9270AB\"></sup>Abel-beth-maacah, and all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9270AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9270AC\"></sup>Chinneroth, with all the land of Naphtali.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And when Baasha heard of it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9271AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9271AD\"></sup>he stopped building Ramah, and he lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9271AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9271AE\"></sup>Tirzah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then King Asa made a proclamation to all Judah, none was exempt, and they carried away the stones of Ramah and its timber, with which Baasha had been building, and with them King Asa built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9272AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9272AF\"></sup>Geba of Benjamin and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9272AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9272AG\"></sup>Mizpah.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9273AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9273AH\"></sup>Now the rest of all the acts of Asa, all his might, and all that he did, and the cities that he built, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? But in his old age he was diseased in his feet.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And Asa slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers in the city of David his father, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9274AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9274AI\"></sup>Jehoshaphat his son reigned in his place.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9275AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9275AJ\"></sup>Nadab the son of Jeroboam began to reign over Israel in the second year of Asa king of Judah, and he reigned over Israel two years.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9276AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9276AK\"></sup>and walked in the way of his father, and in his sin <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9276AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9276AL\"></sup>which he made Israel to sin.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9277AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9277AM\"></sup>Baasha the son of Ahijah, of the house of Issachar, conspired against him. And Baasha struck him down at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9277AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9277AN\"></sup>Gibbethon, which belonged to the Philistines, for Nadab and all Israel were laying siege to Gibbethon.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Baasha killed him in the third year of Asa king of Judah and reigned in his place.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And as soon as he was king, he killed all the house of Jeroboam. He left to the house of Jeroboam not one that breathed, until he had destroyed it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9279AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9279AO\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he spoke by his servant Ahijah the Shilonite.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>It was for the sins of Jeroboam that he sinned and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9280AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9280AP\"></sup>that he made Israel to sin, and because of the anger to which he provoked the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Nadab and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9282AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9282AQ\"></sup>And there was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their days.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>In the third year of Asa king of Judah, Baasha the son of Ahijah began to reign over all Israel at Tirzah, and he reigned twenty-four years.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>He did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9284AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9284AR\"></sup>and walked in the way of Jeroboam and in his sin which he made Israel to sin."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>And the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9285A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9285A\"></sup>Jehu the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9285B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9285B\"></sup>Hanani against Baasha, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Since I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9286C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9286C\"></sup>exalted you out of the dust and made you leader over my people Israel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9286D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9286D\"></sup>you have walked in the way of Jeroboam and have made my people Israel to sin, provoking me to anger with their sins,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>behold, I will utterly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9287E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9287E\"></sup>sweep away <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9287F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9287F\"></sup>Baasha and his house, and I will make your house <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9287G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9287G\"></sup>like the house of Jeroboam the son of Nebat.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9288H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9288H\"></sup>Anyone belonging to Baasha who dies in the city the dogs shall eat, and anyone of his who dies in the field the birds of the heavens shall eat.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Baasha and what he did, and his might, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Baasha slept with his fathers and was buried at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9290I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9290I\"></sup>Tirzah, and Elah his son reigned in his place.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Moreover, the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came by the prophet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9291J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9291J\"></sup>Jehu the son of Hanani against Baasha and his house, both because of all the evil that he did in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, provoking him to anger with the work of his hands, in being like the house of Jeroboam, and also because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9291K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9291K\"></sup>he destroyed it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>In the twenty-sixth year of Asa king of Judah, Elah the son of Baasha began to reign over Israel in Tirzah, and he reigned two years.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But his servant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9293L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9293L\"></sup>Zimri, commander of half his chariots, conspired against him. When he was at Tirzah, drinking himself drunk in the house of Arza, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9293M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9293M\"></sup>who was over the household in Tirzah,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Zimri came in and struck him down and killed him, in the twenty-seventh year of Asa king of Judah, and reigned in his place.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When he began to reign, as soon as he had seated himself on his throne, he struck down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9295N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9295N\"></sup>all the house of Baasha. He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9295O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9295O\"></sup>did not leave him a single male of his relatives or his friends.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Thus Zimri destroyed all the house of Baasha, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9296P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9296P\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which he spoke against Baasha by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9296Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9296Q\"></sup>Jehu the prophet,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>for all the sins of Baasha and the sins of Elah his son, which they sinned and which they made Israel to sin, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9297R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9297R\"></sup>provoking the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel to anger with their idols.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Elah and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>In the twenty-seventh year of Asa king of Judah, Zimri reigned seven days in Tirzah. Now the troops were encamped against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9299S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9299S\"></sup>Gibbethon, which belonged to the Philistines,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and the troops who were encamped heard it said, “Zimri has conspired, and he has killed the king.” Therefore all Israel made Omri, the commander of the army, king over Israel that day in the camp.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So Omri went up from Gibbethon, and all Israel with him, and they besieged Tirzah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And when Zimri saw that the city was taken, he went into the citadel of the king's house and burned the king's house over him with fire and died,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>because of his sins that he committed, doing evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9303T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9303T\"></sup>walking in the way of Jeroboam, and for his sin which he committed, making Israel to sin.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Zimri, and the conspiracy that he made, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the people of Israel were divided into two parts. Half of the people followed Tibni the son of Ginath, to make him king, and half followed Omri.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But the people who followed Omri overcame the people who followed Tibni the son of Ginath. So Tibni died, and Omri became king.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In the thirty-first year of Asa king of Judah, Omri began to reign over Israel, and he reigned for twelve years; six years he reigned in Tirzah.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He bought the hill of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9308U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9308U\"></sup>Samaria from Shemer for two talents of silver, and he fortified the hill and called the name of the city that he built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9308V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9308V\"></sup>Samaria, after the name of Shemer, the owner of the hill.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9309W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9309W\"></sup>Omri did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and did more evil <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9309X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9309X\"></sup>than all who were before him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9310Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9310Y\"></sup>he walked in all the way of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, and in the sins that he made Israel to sin, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9310Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9310Z\"></sup>provoking the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, to anger by their idols.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Omri that he did, and the might that he showed, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And Omri slept with his fathers and was buried in Samaria, and Ahab his son reigned in his place.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>In the thirty-eighth year of Asa king of Judah, Ahab the son of Omri began to reign over Israel, and Ahab the son of Omri reigned over Israel in Samaria twenty-two years.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And Ahab the son of Omri did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9314AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9314AA\"></sup>more than all who were before him.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And as if it had been a light thing for him to walk in the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9315AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9315AB\"></sup>he took for his wife Jezebel the daughter of Ethbaal king of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9315AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9315AC\"></sup>Sidonians, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9315AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9315AD\"></sup>and went and served Baal and worshiped him.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He erected an altar for Baal in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9316AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9316AE\"></sup>the house of Baal, which he built in Samaria.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And Ahab made an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9317AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9317AF\"></sup>Asherah. Ahab did more to provoke the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, to anger <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9317AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9317AG\"></sup>than all the kings of Israel who were before him.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9318AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9318AH\"></sup>In his days Hiel of Bethel built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9318AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9318AI\"></sup>Jericho. He laid its foundation at the cost of Abiram his firstborn, and set up its gates at the cost of his youngest son Segub, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which he spoke by Joshua the son of Nun."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>Now Elijah the Tishbite, of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9319A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9319A\"></sup>Tishbe in Gilead, said to Ahab, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9319B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9319B\"></sup>“As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, lives, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9319C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9319C\"></sup>before whom I stand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9319D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9319D\"></sup>there shall be neither dew nor rain these years, except by my word.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to him:",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Depart from here and turn eastward and hide yourself by the brook Cherith, which is east of the Jordan.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You shall drink from the brook, and I have commanded the ravens to feed you there.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So he went and did according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He went and lived by the brook Cherith that is east of the Jordan.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the ravens brought him bread and meat in the morning, and bread and meat in the evening, and he drank from the brook.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And after a while the brook dried up, because there was no rain in the land.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to him,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Arise, go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9327E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9327E\"></sup>Zarephath, which belongs to Sidon, and dwell there. Behold, I have commanded a widow there to feed you.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So he arose and went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9328F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9328F\"></sup>Zarephath. And when he came to the gate of the city, behold, a widow was there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9328G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9328G\"></sup>gathering sticks. And he called to her and said, “Bring me a little water in a vessel, that I may drink.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And as she was going to bring it, he called to her and said, “Bring me a morsel of bread in your hand.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And she said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9330H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9330H\"></sup>“As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God lives, I have nothing baked, only a handful of flour in a jar and a little oil in a jug. And now I am gathering a couple of sticks that I may go in and prepare it for myself and my son, that we may eat it and die.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Elijah said to her, “Do not fear; go and do as you have said. But first make me a little cake of it and bring it to me, and afterward make something for yourself and your son.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, ‘The jar of flour shall not be spent, and the jug of oil shall not be empty, until the day that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sends rain upon the earth.’”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And she went and did as Elijah said. And she and he and her household ate for many days.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The jar of flour was not spent, neither did the jug of oil become empty, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he spoke by Elijah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>After this the son of the woman, the mistress of the house, became ill. And his illness was so severe that there was no breath left in him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And she said to Elijah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9336I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9336I\"></sup>“What have you against me, O <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9336J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9336J\"></sup>man of God? You have come to me to bring my sin to remembrance and to cause the death of my son!”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And he said to her, “Give me your son.” And he took him from her arms and carried him up into the upper chamber where he lodged, and laid him on his own bed.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And he cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, have you brought calamity even upon the widow with whom I sojourn, by killing her son?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9339K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9339K\"></sup>Then he stretched himself upon the child three times and cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, let this child's life come into him again.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> listened to the voice of Elijah. And the life of the child came into him again, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9340L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9340L\"></sup>he revived.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And Elijah took the child and brought him down from the upper chamber into the house and delivered him to his mother. And Elijah said, “See, your son lives.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the woman said to Elijah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9342M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9342M\"></sup>“Now I know that you are a man of God, and that the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in your mouth is truth.”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9343A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9343A\"></sup>After many days the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Elijah, in the third year, saying, “Go, show yourself to Ahab, and I will send rain upon the earth.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So Elijah went to show himself to Ahab. Now the famine was severe in Samaria.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Ahab called Obadiah, who was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9345B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9345B\"></sup>over the household. (Now Obadiah feared the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> greatly,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9346C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9346C\"></sup>when Jezebel cut off the prophets of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, Obadiah took a hundred prophets and hid them by fifties in a cave and fed them with bread and water.)",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Ahab said to Obadiah, “Go through the land to all the springs of water and to all the valleys. Perhaps we may find grass and save the horses and mules alive, and not lose some of the animals.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So they divided the land between them to pass through it. Ahab went in one direction by himself, and Obadiah went in another direction by himself.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And as Obadiah was on the way, behold, Elijah met him. And Obadiah recognized him and fell on his face and said, “Is it you, my lord Elijah?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And he answered him, “It is I. Go, tell your lord, ‘Behold, Elijah is here.’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And he said, “How have I sinned, that you would give your servant into the hand of Ahab, to kill me?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9352D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9352D\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God lives, there is no nation or kingdom where my lord has not sent to seek you. And when they would say, ‘He is not here,’ he would take an oath of the kingdom or nation, that they had not found you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And now you say, ‘Go, tell your lord, “Behold, Elijah is here.”’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And as soon as I have gone from you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9354E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9354E\"></sup>the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will carry you I know not where. And so, when I come and tell Ahab and he cannot find you, he will kill me, although I your servant have feared the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from my youth.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Has it not been told my lord what I did <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9355F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9355F\"></sup>when Jezebel killed the prophets of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, how I hid a hundred men of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s prophets by fifties in a cave and fed them with bread and water?",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And now you say, ‘Go, tell your lord, “Behold, Elijah is here”’; and he will kill me.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Elijah said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9357G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9357G\"></sup>“As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts lives, before whom I stand, I will surely show myself to him today.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So Obadiah went to meet Ahab, and told him. And Ahab went to meet Elijah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When Ahab saw Elijah, Ahab said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9359H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9359H\"></sup>“Is it you, you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9359I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9359I\"></sup>troubler of Israel?”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And he answered, “I have not troubled Israel, but you have, and your father's house, because you have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9360J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9360J\"></sup>abandoned the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9360K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9360K\"></sup>followed the Baals.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now therefore send and gather all Israel to me at Mount <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9361L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9361L\"></sup>Carmel, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9361M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9361M\"></sup>450 prophets of Baal and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9361N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9361N\"></sup>the 400 prophets of Asherah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9361O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9361O\"></sup>who eat at Jezebel's table.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Ahab sent to all the people of Israel and gathered the prophets together at Mount Carmel.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And Elijah came near to all the people and said, “How long <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9363P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9363P\"></sup>will you go limping between two different opinions? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9363Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9363Q\"></sup>If the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is God, follow him; but if Baal, then follow him.” And the people did not answer him a word.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Elijah said to the people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9364R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9364R\"></sup>“I, even I only, am left a prophet of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but Baal's prophets are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9364S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9364S\"></sup>450 men.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Let two bulls be given to us, and let them choose one bull for themselves and cut it in pieces and lay it on the wood, but put no fire to it. And I will prepare the other bull and lay it on the wood and put no fire to it.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And you call upon the name of your god, and I will call upon the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the God who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9366T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9366T\"></sup>answers by fire, he is God.” And all the people answered, “It is well spoken.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Elijah said to the prophets of Baal, “Choose for yourselves one bull and prepare it first, for you are many, and call upon the name of your god, but put no fire to it.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And they took the bull that was given them, and they prepared it and called upon the name of Baal from morning until noon, saying, “O Baal, answer us!” But there was no voice, and no one answered. And they limped around the altar that they had made.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And at noon Elijah mocked them, saying, “Cry aloud, for he is a god. Either he is musing, or he is relieving himself, or he is on a journey, or perhaps he is asleep and must be awakened.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And they cried aloud and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9370U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9370U\"></sup>cut themselves after their custom with swords and lances, until the blood gushed out upon them.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And as midday passed, they raved on until the time of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9371V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9371V\"></sup>the offering of the oblation, but there was no voice. No one answered; no one paid attention.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Elijah said to all the people, “Come near to me.” And all the people came near to him. And he repaired the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that had been <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9372W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9372W\"></sup>thrown down.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Elijah took twelve stones, according to the number of the tribes of the sons of Jacob, to whom the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9373X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9373X\"></sup>“Israel shall be your name,”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>and with the stones he built an altar in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And he made a trench about the altar, as great as would contain two seahs of seed.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9375Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9375Y\"></sup>And he put the wood in order and cut the bull in pieces and laid it on the wood. And he said, “Fill four jars with water and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9375Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9375Z\"></sup>pour it on the burnt offering and on the wood.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And he said, “Do it a second time.” And they did it a second time. And he said, “Do it a third time.” And they did it a third time.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And the water ran around the altar and filled the trench also with water.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And at the time of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9378AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9378AA\"></sup>the offering of the oblation, Elijah the prophet came near and said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9378AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9378AB\"></sup>God of Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, let it be known this day that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9378AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9378AC\"></sup>you are God in Israel, and that I am your servant, and that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9378AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9378AD\"></sup>I have done all these things at your word.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Answer me, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, answer me, that this people may know that you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, are God, and that you have turned their hearts back.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9380AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9380AE\"></sup>Then the fire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> fell and consumed the burnt offering and the wood and the stones and the dust, and licked up the water that was in the trench.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And when all the people saw it, they fell on their faces and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9381AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9381AF\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he is God; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he is God.”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And Elijah said to them, “Seize the prophets of Baal; let not one of them escape.” And they seized them. And Elijah brought them down to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9382AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9382AG\"></sup>the brook Kishon and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9382AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9382AH\"></sup>slaughtered them there.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And Elijah said to Ahab, “Go up, eat and drink, for there is a sound of the rushing of rain.”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>So Ahab went up to eat and to drink. And Elijah went up to the top of Mount Carmel. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9384AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9384AI\"></sup>And he bowed himself down on the earth and put his face between his knees.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And he said to his servant, “Go up now, look toward the sea.” And he went up and looked and said, “There is nothing.” And he said, “Go again,” seven times.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>And at the seventh time he said, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9386AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9386AJ\"></sup>a little cloud like a man's hand is rising from the sea.” And he said, “Go up, say to Ahab, ‘Prepare your chariot and go down, lest the rain stop you.’”",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>And in a little while the heavens grew black with clouds and wind, and there was a great rain. And Ahab rode and went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9387AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9387AK\"></sup>Jezreel.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9388AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9388AL\"></sup>And the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was on Elijah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9388AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9388AM\"></sup>and he gathered up his garment and ran before Ahab to the entrance of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9388AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9388AN\"></sup>Jezreel."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>Ahab told Jezebel all that Elijah had done, and how <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9389A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9389A\"></sup>he had killed all the prophets with the sword.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then Jezebel sent a messenger to Elijah, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9390B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9390B\"></sup>“So may the gods do to me and more also, if I do not make your life as the life of one of them by this time tomorrow.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then he was afraid, and he arose and ran for his life and came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9391C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9391C\"></sup>Beersheba, which belongs to Judah, and left his servant there.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But he himself went a day's journey into the wilderness and came and sat down under a broom tree. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9392D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9392D\"></sup>And he asked that he might die, saying, “It is enough; now, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, take away my life, for I am no better than my fathers.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And he lay down and slept under a broom tree. And behold, an angel touched him and said to him, “Arise and eat.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he looked, and behold, there was at his head a cake baked on hot stones and a jar of water. And he ate and drank and lay down again.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came again a second time and touched him and said, “Arise and eat, for the journey is too great for you.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And he arose and ate and drank, and went in the strength of that food <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9396E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9396E\"></sup>forty days and forty nights to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9396F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9396F\"></sup>Horeb, the mount of God.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>There he came to a cave and lodged in it. And behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9397G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9397G\"></sup>the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to him, and he said to him, “What are you doing here, Elijah?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He said, “I have been very <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9398H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9398H\"></sup>jealous for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of hosts. For the people of Israel have forsaken your covenant, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9398I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9398I\"></sup>thrown down your altars, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9398J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9398J\"></sup>killed your prophets with the sword, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9398K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9398K\"></sup>and I, even I only, am left, and they seek my life, to take it away.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And he said, “Go out and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9399L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9399L\"></sup>stand on the mount before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And behold, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> passed by, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9399M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9399M\"></sup>a great and strong wind tore the mountains and broke in pieces the rocks before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was not in the wind. And after the wind <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9399N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9399N\"></sup>an earthquake, but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was not in the earthquake.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And after the earthquake a fire, but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was not in the fire. And after the fire the sound of a low whisper.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And when Elijah heard it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9401O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9401O\"></sup>he wrapped his face in his cloak and went out and stood at the entrance of the cave. And behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9401P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9401P\"></sup>there came a voice to him and said, “What are you doing here, Elijah?”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9402Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9402Q\"></sup>“I have been very jealous for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of hosts. For the people of Israel have forsaken your covenant, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9402R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9402R\"></sup>thrown down your altars, and killed your prophets with the sword, and I, even I only, am left, and they seek my life, to take it away.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Go, return on your way to the wilderness of Damascus. And when you arrive, you shall anoint Hazael to be king over Syria.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9404S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9404S\"></sup>And Jehu the son of Nimshi you shall anoint to be king over Israel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9404T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9404T\"></sup>Elisha the son of Shaphat of Abel-meholah you shall anoint to be prophet in your place.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the one who escapes from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9405U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9405U\"></sup>the sword of Hazael <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9405V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9405V\"></sup>shall Jehu put to death, and the one who escapes from the sword of Jehu <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9405W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9405W\"></sup>shall Elisha put to death.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9406X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9406X\"></sup>Yet I will leave seven thousand in Israel, all the knees that have not bowed to Baal, and every mouth that has not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9406Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9406Y\"></sup>kissed him.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So he departed from there and found Elisha the son of Shaphat, who was plowing with twelve yoke of oxen in front of him, and he was with the twelfth. Elijah passed by him and cast <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9407Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9407Z\"></sup>his cloak upon him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And he left the oxen and ran after Elijah and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9408AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9408AA\"></sup>“Let me kiss my father and my mother, and then I will follow you.” And he said to him, “Go back again, for what have I done to you?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And he returned from following him and took the yoke of oxen and sacrificed them and boiled their flesh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9409AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9409AB\"></sup>with the yokes of the oxen and gave it to the people, and they ate. Then he arose and went after Elijah and assisted him."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9410A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9410A\"></sup>Ben-hadad the king of Syria gathered all his army together. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9410B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9410B\"></sup>Thirty-two kings were with him, and horses and chariots. And he went up and closed in on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9410C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9410C\"></sup>Samaria and fought against it.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he sent messengers into the city to Ahab king of Israel and said to him, “Thus says Ben-hadad:",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>‘Your silver and your gold are mine; your best wives and children also are mine.’”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And the king of Israel answered, “As you say, my lord, O king, I am yours, and all that I have.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The messengers came again and said, “Thus says Ben-hadad: ‘I sent to you, saying, “Deliver to me your silver and your gold, your wives and your children.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Nevertheless I will send my servants to you tomorrow about this time, and they shall search your house and the houses of your servants and lay hands on whatever pleases you and take it away.’”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the king of Israel called all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9416D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9416D\"></sup>elders of the land and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9416E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9416E\"></sup>“Mark, now, and see how this man is seeking trouble, for he sent to me for my wives and my children, and for my silver and my gold, and I did not refuse him.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And all the elders and all the people said to him, “Do not listen or consent.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So he said to the messengers of Ben-hadad, “Tell my lord the king, ‘All that you first demanded of your servant I will do, but this thing I cannot do.’” And the messengers departed and brought him word again.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Ben-hadad sent to him and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9419F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9419F\"></sup>“The gods do so to me and more also, if the dust of Samaria shall suffice for handfuls for all the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9419G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9419G\"></sup>who follow me.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the king of Israel answered, “Tell him, ‘Let not him who straps on his armor boast himself as he who takes it off.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When Ben-hadad heard this message as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9421H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9421H\"></sup>he was drinking with the kings in the booths, he said to his men, “Take your positions.” And they took their positions against the city.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And behold, a prophet came near to Ahab king of Israel and said, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, Have you seen all this great multitude? Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9422I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9422I\"></sup>I will give it into your hand this day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9422J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9422J\"></sup>and you shall know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And Ahab said, “By whom?” He said, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, By the servants of the governors of the districts.” Then he said, “Who shall begin the battle?” He answered, “You.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then he mustered the servants of the governors of the districts, and they were 232. And after them he mustered all the people of Israel, seven thousand.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And they went out at noon, while Ben-hadad <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9425K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9425K\"></sup>was drinking himself drunk in the booths, he and the thirty-two kings who helped him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The servants of the governors of the districts went out first. And Ben-hadad sent out scouts, and they reported to him, “Men are coming out from Samaria.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He said, “If they have come out for peace, take them alive. Or if they have come out for war, take them alive.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So these went out of the city, the servants of the governors of the districts and the army that followed them.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And each struck down his man. The Syrians fled, and Israel pursued them, but Ben-hadad king of Syria escaped on a horse with horsemen.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the king of Israel went out and struck the horses and chariots, and struck the Syrians with a great blow.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9431L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9431L\"></sup>the prophet came near to the king of Israel and said to him, “Come, strengthen yourself, and consider well what you have to do, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9431M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9431M\"></sup>in the spring the king of Syria will come up against you.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the servants of the king of Syria said to him, “Their gods are gods of the hills, and so they were stronger than we. But let us fight against them in the plain, and surely we shall be stronger than they.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And do this: remove the kings, each from his post, and put commanders in their places,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and muster an army like the army that you have lost, horse for horse, and chariot for chariot. Then we will fight against them in the plain, and surely we shall be stronger than they.” And he listened to their voice and did so.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9435N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9435N\"></sup>In the spring, Ben-hadad mustered the Syrians and went up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9435O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9435O\"></sup>Aphek to fight against Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And the people of Israel were mustered and were provisioned and went against them. The people of Israel encamped before them like two little flocks of goats, but the Syrians filled the country.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9437P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9437P\"></sup>man of God came near and said to the king of Israel, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘Because the Syrians have said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9437Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9437Q\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is a god of the hills but he is not a god of the valleys,” therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9437R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9437R\"></sup>I will give all this great multitude into your hand, and you shall know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And they encamped opposite one another seven days. Then on the seventh day the battle was joined. And the people of Israel struck down of the Syrians 100,000 foot soldiers in one day.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And the rest fled into the city of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9439S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9439S\"></sup>Aphek, and the wall fell upon 27,000 men who were left.Ben-hadad also fled and entered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9439T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9439T\"></sup>an inner chamber in the city.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And his servants said to him, “Behold now, we have heard that the kings of the house of Israel are merciful kings. Let us <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9440U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9440U\"></sup>put sackcloth around our waists and ropes on our heads and go out to the king of Israel. Perhaps he will spare your life.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9441V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9441V\"></sup>tied sackcloth around their waists and put ropes on their heads and went to the king of Israel and said, “Your servant Ben-hadad says, ‘Please, let me live.’” And he said, “Does he still live? He is my brother.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Now the men were watching for a sign, and they quickly took it up from him and said, “Yes, your brother Ben-hadad.” Then he said, “Go and bring him.” Then Ben-hadad came out to him, and he caused him to come up into the chariot.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And Ben-hadad said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9443W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9443W\"></sup>“The cities that my father took from your father I will restore, and you may establish bazaars for yourself in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9443X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9443X\"></sup>Damascus, as my father did in Samaria.” And Ahab said, “I will let you go on these terms.” So he made a covenant with him and let him go.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And a certain man of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9444Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9444Y\"></sup>the sons of the prophets said to his fellow <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9444Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9444Z\"></sup>at the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Strike me, please.” But the man refused to strike him.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then he said to him, “Because you have not obeyed the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, behold, as soon as you have gone from me, a lion shall strike you down.” And as soon as he had departed from him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9445AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9445AA\"></sup>a lion met him and struck him down.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then he found another man and said, “Strike me, please.” And the man struck him—struck him and wounded him.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>So the prophet departed and waited for the king by the way, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9447AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9447AB\"></sup>disguising himself with a bandage over his eyes.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And as the king passed, he cried to the king and said, “Your servant went out into the midst of the battle, and behold, a soldier turned and brought a man to me and said, ‘Guard this man; if by any means he is missing, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9448AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9448AC\"></sup>your life shall be for his life, or else you shall pay a talent of silver.’",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And as your servant was busy here and there, he was gone.” The king of Israel said to him, “So shall your judgment be; you yourself have decided it.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Then he hurried to take the bandage away from his eyes, and the king of Israel recognized him as one of the prophets.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And he said to him, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘Because you have let go out of your hand the man whom I had devoted to destruction, therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9451AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9451AD\"></sup>your life shall be for his life, and your people for his people.’”",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And the king of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9452AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9452AE\"></sup>went to his house vexed and sullen and came to Samaria."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>Now Naboth the Jezreelite had a vineyard in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9453A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9453A\"></sup>Jezreel, beside the palace of Ahab king of Samaria.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And after this Ahab said to Naboth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9454B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9454B\"></sup>“Give me your vineyard, that I may have it for a vegetable garden, because it is near my house, and I will give you a better vineyard for it; or, if it seems good to you, I will give you its value in money.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But Naboth said to Ahab, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forbid <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9455C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9455C\"></sup>that I should give you the inheritance of my fathers.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And Ahab <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9456D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9456D\"></sup>went into his house vexed and sullen because of what Naboth the Jezreelite had said to him, for he had said, “I will not give you the inheritance of my fathers.” And he lay down on his bed and turned away his face and would eat no food.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But Jezebel his wife came to him and said to him, “Why is your spirit so vexed that you eat no food?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he said to her, “Because I spoke to Naboth the Jezreelite and said to him, ‘Give me your vineyard for money, or else, if it please you, I will give you another vineyard for it.’ And he answered, ‘I will not give you my vineyard.’”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Jezebel his wife said to him, “Do you now govern Israel? Arise and eat bread and let your heart be cheerful; I will give you the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9460E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9460E\"></sup>So she wrote letters in Ahab's name and sealed them with his seal, and she sent the letters to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9460F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9460F\"></sup>the elders and the leaders who lived with Naboth in his city.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And she wrote in the letters, “Proclaim a fast, and set Naboth at the head of the people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And set two <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9462G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9462G\"></sup>worthless men opposite him, and let them bring a charge against him, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9462H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9462H\"></sup>‘You have cursed God and the king.’ Then take him out and stone him to death.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the men of his city, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9463I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9463I\"></sup>the elders and the leaders who lived in his city, did as Jezebel had sent word to them. As it was written in the letters that she had sent to them,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9464J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9464J\"></sup>they proclaimed a fast and set Naboth at the head of the people.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the two worthless men came in and sat opposite him. And the worthless men brought a charge against Naboth in the presence of the people, saying, “Naboth cursed God and the king.” So they took him outside the city and stoned him to death with stones.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then they sent to Jezebel, saying, “Naboth has been stoned; he is dead.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>As soon as Jezebel heard that Naboth had been stoned and was dead, Jezebel said to Ahab, “Arise, take possession of the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite, which he refused to give you for money, for Naboth is not alive, but dead.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And as soon as Ahab heard that Naboth was dead, Ahab arose to go down to the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite, to take possession of it.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9469K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9469K\"></sup>Then the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Elijah the Tishbite, saying,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Arise, go down to meet Ahab king of Israel, who is in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9470L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9470L\"></sup>Samaria; behold, he is in the vineyard of Naboth, where he has gone to take possession.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And you shall say to him, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Have you killed and also taken possession?”’ And you shall say to him, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9471M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9471M\"></sup>“In the place where dogs licked up the blood of Naboth shall dogs lick your own blood.”’”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Ahab said to Elijah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9472N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9472N\"></sup>“Have you found me, O my enemy?” He answered, “I have found you, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9472O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9472O\"></sup>you have sold yourself to do what is evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Behold, I will bring disaster upon you. I will utterly burn you up, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9473P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9473P\"></sup>will cut off from Ahab every male, bond or free, in Israel.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And I will make your house like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9474Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9474Q\"></sup>the house of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, and like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9474R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9474R\"></sup>the house of Baasha the son of Ahijah, for the anger to which you have provoked me, and because you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9474S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9474S\"></sup>have made Israel to sin.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And of Jezebel the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> also said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9475T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9475T\"></sup>‘The dogs shall eat Jezebel within <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9475U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9475U\"></sup>the walls of Jezreel.’",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9476V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9476V\"></sup>Anyone belonging to Ahab who dies in the city the dogs shall eat, and anyone of his who dies in the open country the birds of the heavens shall eat.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>(<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9477W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9477W\"></sup>There was none who sold himself to do what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> like Ahab, whom Jezebel his wife incited.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He acted very abominably in going after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9478X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9478X\"></sup>idols, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9478Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9478Y\"></sup>the Amorites had done, whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> cast out before the people of Israel.)",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And when Ahab heard those words, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9479Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9479Z\"></sup>tore his clothes and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9479AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9479AA\"></sup>put sackcloth on his flesh and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9479AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9479AB\"></sup>fasted and lay in sackcloth and went about dejectedly.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Elijah the Tishbite, saying,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“Have you seen how Ahab has humbled himself before me? Because he has humbled himself before me, I will not bring the disaster in his days; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9481AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9481AC\"></sup>but in his son's days I will bring the disaster upon his house.”"
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>For three years Syria and Israel continued without war.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9483A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9483A\"></sup>But in the third year <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9483B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9483B\"></sup>Jehoshaphat the king of Judah came down to the king of Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And the king of Israel said to his servants, “Do you know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9484C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9484C\"></sup>Ramoth-gilead belongs to us, and we keep quiet and do not take it out of the hand of the king of Syria?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And he said to Jehoshaphat, “Will you go with me to battle at Ramoth-gilead?” And Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9485D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9485D\"></sup>“I am as you are, my people as your people, my horses as your horses.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, “Inquire first for the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the king of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9487E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9487E\"></sup>gathered the prophets together, about four hundred men, and said to them, “Shall I go to battle against Ramoth-gilead, or shall I refrain?” And they said, “Go up, for the Lord will give it into the hand of the king.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9488F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9488F\"></sup>Jehoshaphat said, “Is there not here another prophet of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of whom we may inquire?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “There is yet one man by whom we may inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, Micaiah the son of Imlah, but I hate him, for he never prophesies good concerning me, but evil.” And Jehoshaphat said, “Let not the king say so.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the king of Israel summoned an officer and said, “Bring quickly Micaiah the son of Imlah.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah were sitting on their thrones, arrayed in their robes, at the threshing floor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9491G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9491G\"></sup>at the entrance of the gate of Samaria, and all the prophets were prophesying before them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah made for himself <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9492H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9492H\"></sup>horns of iron and said, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘With these <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9492I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9492I\"></sup>you shall push the Syrians until they are destroyed.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And all the prophets prophesied so and said, “Go up to Ramoth-gilead and triumph; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give it into the hand of the king.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the messenger who went to summon Micaiah said to him, “Behold, the words of the prophets with one accord are favorable to the king. Let your word be like the word of one of them, and speak favorably.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But Micaiah said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9495J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9495J\"></sup>“As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9495K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9495K\"></sup>what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says to me, that I will speak.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And when he had come to the king, the king said to him, “Micaiah, shall we go to Ramoth-gilead to battle, or shall we refrain?” And he answered him, “Go up and triumph; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give it into the hand of the king.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But the king said to him, “How many times shall I make you swear that you speak to me nothing but the truth in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he said, “I saw all Israel scattered on the mountains, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9498L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9498L\"></sup>as sheep that have no shepherd. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, ‘These have no master; let each return to his home in peace.’”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9499M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9499M\"></sup>“Did I not tell you that he would not prophesy good concerning me, but evil?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And Micaiah said, “Therefore hear the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9500N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9500N\"></sup>I saw the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sitting on his throne, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9500O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9500O\"></sup>and all the host of heaven standing beside him on his right hand and on his left;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, ‘Who will entice Ahab, that he may go up and fall at Ramoth-gilead?’ And one said one thing, and another said another.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then a spirit came forward and stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, ‘I will entice him.’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, ‘By what means?’ And he said, ‘I will go out, and will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9503P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9503P\"></sup>a lying spirit in the mouth of all his prophets.’ And he said, ‘You are to entice him, and you shall succeed; go out and do so.’",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now therefore behold, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has put a lying spirit in the mouth of all these your prophets; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has declared disaster for you.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah came near <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9505Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9505Q\"></sup>and struck Micaiah on the cheek and said, “How did the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> go from me to speak to you?”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And Micaiah said, “Behold, you shall see on that day when you go <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9506R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9506R\"></sup>into an inner chamber to hide yourself.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And the king of Israel said, “Seize Micaiah, and take him back to Amon the governor of the city and to Joash the king's son,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and say, ‘Thus says the king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9508S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9508S\"></sup>“Put this fellow in prison and feed him meager rations of bread and water, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9508T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9508T\"></sup>until I come in peace.”’”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And Micaiah said, “If you return in peace, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9509U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9509U\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not spoken by me.” And he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9509V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9509V\"></sup>“Hear, all you peoples!”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah went up to Ramoth-gilead.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9511W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9511W\"></sup>“I will disguise myself and go into battle, but you wear your robes.” And the king of Israel disguised himself and went into battle.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Now the king of Syria had commanded <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9512X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9512X\"></sup>the thirty-two captains of his chariots, “Fight with neither small nor great, but only with the king of Israel.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And when the captains of the chariots saw Jehoshaphat, they said, “It is surely the king of Israel.” So they turned to fight against him. And Jehoshaphat cried out.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And when the captains of the chariots saw that it was not the king of Israel, they turned back from pursuing him.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But a certain man drew his bow at random and struck the king of Israel between the scale armor and the breastplate. Therefore he said to the driver of his chariot, “Turn around and carry me out of the battle, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9515Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9515Y\"></sup>for I am wounded.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And the battle continued that day, and the king was propped up in his chariot facing the Syrians, until at evening he died. And the blood of the wound flowed into the bottom of the chariot.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And about sunset a cry went through the army, “Every man to his city, and every man to his country!”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>So the king died, and was brought to Samaria. And they buried the king in Samaria.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And they washed the chariot by the pool of Samaria, and the dogs licked up his blood, and the prostitutes washed themselves in it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9519Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9519Z\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he had spoken.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Ahab and all that he did, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9520AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9520AA\"></sup>the ivory house that he built and all the cities that he built, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>So Ahab slept with his fathers, and Ahaziah his son reigned in his place.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9522AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9522AB\"></sup>Jehoshaphat the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9522AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9522AC\"></sup>Asa began to reign over Judah in the fourth year of Ahab king of Israel.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Jehoshaphat was thirty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned twenty-five years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Azubah the daughter of Shilhi.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9524AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9524AD\"></sup>He walked in all the way of Asa his father. He did not turn aside from it, doing what was right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9524AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9524AE\"></sup>the high places were not taken away, and the people still sacrificed and made offerings on the high places.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9525AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9525AF\"></sup>Jehoshaphat also made peace with the king of Israel.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jehoshaphat, and his might that he showed, and how he warred, are they not written <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9526AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9526AG\"></sup>in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>And from the land he exterminated the remnant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9527AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9527AH\"></sup>of the male cult prostitutes who remained in the days of his father Asa.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9528AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9528AI\"></sup>There was no king in Edom; a deputy was king.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Jehoshaphat made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9529AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9529AJ\"></sup>ships of Tarshish to go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9529AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9529AK\"></sup>Ophir for gold, but they did not go, for the ships were wrecked at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9529AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9529AL\"></sup>Ezion-geber.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Then Ahaziah the son of Ahab said to Jehoshaphat, “Let my servants go with your servants in the ships,” but Jehoshaphat was not willing.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9531AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9531AM\"></sup>And Jehoshaphat slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers in the city of David his father, and Jehoram his son reigned in his place.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Ahaziah the son of Ahab <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9532AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9532AN\"></sup>began to reign over Israel in Samaria in the seventeenth year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, and he reigned two years over Israel.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>He did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9533AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9533AO\"></sup>and walked in the way of his father and in the way of his mother and in the way of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who made Israel to sin.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9534AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9534AP\"></sup>He served Baal and worshiped him and provoked the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, to anger <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9534AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9534AQ\"></sup>in every way that his father had done."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;